1
00:00:01,043 --> 00:00:02,795
[computer beeping, clicking]

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:07,000

3
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:09,592
- [William] <i>Here we go.</i>
- [mouse clicks]

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,000

5
00:00:09,593 --> 00:00:12,763
["Keep Your Head Up"
by Wolfgang Valbrun playing]

6
00:00:27,737 --> 00:00:29,363
<i>All right, all right,
all right.</i>

7
00:00:30,573 --> 00:00:31,574
Did you miss me?

8
00:00:32,324 --> 00:00:33,492
Did you miss me?

9
00:00:34,243 --> 00:00:35,702
[computer chimes]

10
00:00:35,703 --> 00:00:37,079
William Radford.

11
00:00:38,330 --> 00:00:39,582
- [computer chimes]
- Okay.

12
00:00:40,291 --> 00:00:42,792
<i>♪ Introspection,
doubtful thoughts ♪</i>

13
00:00:42,793 --> 00:00:44,503
<i>♪ They weaken men ♪</i>

14
00:00:46,172 --> 00:00:50,384
<i>♪ While the tyrants
manipulate and poison them ♪</i>

15
00:00:52,136 --> 00:00:54,763
<i>♪ Fatal attraction,
desire's such a fickle thing ♪</i>

16
00:00:54,764 --> 00:00:55,765
Hmm.

17
00:00:58,017 --> 00:01:02,312
<i>♪ No satisfaction
if you let yourself give in ♪</i>

18
00:01:02,313 --> 00:01:03,355
<i>♪ Keep your head up ♪</i>

19
00:01:08,235 --> 00:01:09,278
<i>♪ Keep your head up ♪</i>

20
00:01:14,283 --> 00:01:15,867
<i>♪ Keep your head up... ♪</i>

21
00:01:15,868 --> 00:01:20,538
[siren wailing]

22
00:01:20,539 --> 00:01:22,165
[woman] <i>You ran out
of the house this morning,</i>

23
00:01:22,166 --> 00:01:23,918
<i>but I need you to get the kids
to school.</i>

24
00:01:32,968 --> 00:01:35,595
<i>♪ We're all kings
and queens within ♪</i>

25
00:01:35,596 --> 00:01:36,806
<i>♪ Keep your head up... ♪</i>

26
00:01:39,642 --> 00:01:42,018
[man 1] <i>My battery's dying.
I'm sure I'm being spied on.</i>

27
00:01:42,019 --> 00:01:43,562
[man 2] <i>Shut up, man.
You're just paranoid.</i>

28
00:01:46,315 --> 00:01:48,107
<i>♪ A great disaster ♪</i>

29
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:50,653
<i>♪ Distracts from boredom
ahead ♪</i>

30
00:01:52,196 --> 00:01:53,822
<i>♪ Fire and brimstone ♪</i>

31
00:01:53,823 --> 00:01:56,575
<i>♪ A warning of nothing
for men ♪</i>

32
00:01:58,369 --> 00:02:00,161
<i>♪ Are you complicit? ♪</i>

33
00:02:00,162 --> 00:02:02,832
<i>♪ Or will you be there
to defend? ♪</i>

34
00:02:04,375 --> 00:02:08,670
<i>♪ Legitimize the lack
of empathy within ♪</i>

35
00:02:08,671 --> 00:02:09,713
<i>♪ Keep your head up ♪</i>

36
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:15,845
<i>♪ Keep your head up ♪</i>

37
00:02:20,850 --> 00:02:21,892
<i>♪ Keep your head up ♪</i>

38
00:02:26,939 --> 00:02:28,023
<i>♪ Keep your head up ♪</i>

39
00:02:31,527 --> 00:02:35,488
[ringtone playing]

40
00:02:35,489 --> 00:02:39,325
<i>♪ If you want to do
your thing... ♪</i>

41
00:02:39,326 --> 00:02:40,327
[song stops]

42
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:46,250
Good morning. What's up?

43
00:02:47,001 --> 00:02:48,418
<i>Look. Take a look at this.</i>

44
00:02:48,419 --> 00:02:50,587
[thunder crashing]

45
00:02:50,588 --> 00:02:52,089
<i>Any noise about it on your end?</i>

46
00:02:52,673 --> 00:02:54,757
[William] No.
I watch people, not weather.

47
00:02:54,758 --> 00:02:57,552
[wind howling]

48
00:02:57,553 --> 00:02:59,220
[Sandra] <i>I've never seen
global storms like this.</i>

49
00:02:59,221 --> 00:03:00,930
<i>We can't figure out
what's causing</i>

50
00:03:00,931 --> 00:03:02,474
<i>this atmospheric phenomena.</i>

51
00:03:03,434 --> 00:03:05,184
<i>Something is way off.</i>

52
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:07,020
<i>Their size, the amount...</i>
[sighs] <i>All of it,</i>

53
00:03:07,021 --> 00:03:08,730
<i>it just doesn't...
doesn't make sense.</i>

54
00:03:08,731 --> 00:03:10,481
[William] All right,
that's crazy right there.

55
00:03:10,482 --> 00:03:12,609
[Sandra] <i>All of NASA's
satellites are blind.</i>

56
00:03:12,610 --> 00:03:14,944
<i>We haven't been able to see
anything for two days.</i>

57
00:03:14,945 --> 00:03:17,405
<i>Can't figure it out.</i>

58
00:03:17,406 --> 00:03:18,656
Yeah.

59
00:03:18,657 --> 00:03:20,199
Well, I got bigger fish to fry

60
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,701
than watching clouds.

61
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:24,788
Look, duty calls,
so just keep me posted.

62
00:03:43,307 --> 00:03:44,975
[distorted voice speaking]

63
00:03:53,901 --> 00:03:56,110
- [William] Not on my watch.
- [distorted voice]
<i>Everywhere we go,</i>

64
00:03:56,111 --> 00:03:59,405
<i>everything we say,
watch, read, and write</i>

65
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:03,493
<i>is captured and evaluated
to censor our awareness
of the truth</i>

66
00:04:03,494 --> 00:04:05,244
<i>and to enslave us</i>

67
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:07,789
<i>to tyrannical, authoritarian
government control.</i>

68
00:04:07,790 --> 00:04:09,374
Okay, Guardian.

69
00:04:09,375 --> 00:04:11,584
[distorted voice]
<i>The surveillance state has also</i>

70
00:04:11,585 --> 00:04:13,836
<i>not revealed that
the Goliath program</i>

71
00:04:13,837 --> 00:04:16,255
<i>is an existential threat
to humanity</i>

72
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:19,133
<i>that no one can
possibly comprehend.</i>

73
00:04:19,134 --> 00:04:22,595
<i>You will see
all the alarming details
in full disclosure</i>

74
00:04:22,596 --> 00:04:25,516
<i>in the Goliath documents
that I'm releasing
to the world.</i>

75
00:04:26,517 --> 00:04:30,395
[William]
All right, now let's go
to suspect number two.

76
00:04:30,396 --> 00:04:31,397
[Faith, faintly] <i>Thank you.</i>

77
00:04:41,156 --> 00:04:43,200
[line ringing]

78
00:04:49,873 --> 00:04:52,291
<i>- Hey.</i>
- A muffin?

79
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:54,627
Really? A muffin?
What are you thinking?

80
00:04:54,628 --> 00:04:56,921
Jesus, Dad. How many times
have we been through this?

81
00:04:56,922 --> 00:04:58,506
One hard-boiled egg.

82
00:04:58,507 --> 00:05:00,508
All right? They're right next
to the doughnuts.

83
00:05:00,509 --> 00:05:01,510
Would it kill you?

84
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:05,221
- You need more protein.
<i>- I need to get to work.</i>

85
00:05:05,222 --> 00:05:07,015
No, you need to lay off
the soy milk.

86
00:05:07,016 --> 00:05:09,475
You haven't had any protein
this week.

87
00:05:09,476 --> 00:05:12,895
- How do you know?
- Let's just say me
and your fridge is pretty tight.

88
00:05:12,896 --> 00:05:14,230
<i>You hacked my fridge?</i>

89
00:05:14,231 --> 00:05:16,107
<i>- Dad.</i>
- Lay off of that stuff.

90
00:05:16,108 --> 00:05:18,192
It's no good for the baby.

91
00:05:18,193 --> 00:05:20,069
- It has zero calcium.
<i>- Uh, it does have calcium.</i>

92
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:21,655
<i>I majored in bio, remember?</i>

93
00:05:23,574 --> 00:05:24,575
Hold on.

94
00:05:26,618 --> 00:05:28,119
Just what I've been waiting for.

95
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,121
You little punk, I got you.

96
00:05:30,414 --> 00:05:33,833
[Faith]
<i>I see you took the Sunday
graveyard shift again.</i>

97
00:05:33,834 --> 00:05:35,710
<i>When's the last time
you left the office?</i>

98
00:05:35,711 --> 00:05:38,296
- That's classified.
<i>- You need to get some sun.</i>

99
00:05:38,297 --> 00:05:41,633
<i>I don't know what looks worse,
you or your poor plant
over there.</i>

100
00:05:44,428 --> 00:05:46,679
<i>- Dad?</i>
- I just... got to focus

101
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,556
on this right here real quick.

102
00:05:48,557 --> 00:05:50,475
<i>Um, I, uh, got to get back</i>

103
00:05:50,476 --> 00:05:52,435
<i>to the lab and finish up
my project.</i>

104
00:05:52,436 --> 00:05:53,437
All right, I love you.

105
00:06:06,116 --> 00:06:07,117
[ringtone playing]

106
00:06:12,206 --> 00:06:13,707
<i>Yo. Did you delete my game?</i>

107
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:16,417
You know you're wasting
your time with that game.

108
00:06:16,418 --> 00:06:18,503
[laughs]
<i>Dad, playing video games</i>

109
00:06:18,504 --> 00:06:20,171
<i>- is my job.</i>
- [ringtone playing]

110
00:06:20,172 --> 00:06:22,298
<i>I'm a tech visionary
in a pre-funding stage.</i>

111
00:06:22,299 --> 00:06:24,134
A tech to who the what?

112
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:28,346
All I know is I've been
pre-funding your ass for years

113
00:06:28,347 --> 00:06:30,014
and you need to get a real job.

114
00:06:30,015 --> 00:06:31,308
This is my job.

115
00:06:33,352 --> 00:06:37,021
Look, son, I got a friend
over at NSA.

116
00:06:37,022 --> 00:06:38,815
- They're recruiting next month.
<i>- Let it go.</i>

117
00:06:38,816 --> 00:06:40,942
<i>I mean, spying on what's
in people's Amazon carts?</i>

118
00:06:40,943 --> 00:06:42,985
Is that what you think I do?

119
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:45,363
<i>- I'm sorry,
did you get promoted?</i>
- Listen, smart-ass.

120
00:06:45,364 --> 00:06:47,782
I know people would rather have
someone watch them...

121
00:06:47,783 --> 00:06:49,742
<i>- Really? That's the choice?</i>
- ...than blow them up.

122
00:06:49,743 --> 00:06:51,744
<i>Give up our privacy or death?</i>

123
00:06:51,745 --> 00:06:54,497
Yep. I think it's a pretty
fair trade, if you ask me.

124
00:06:54,498 --> 00:06:55,915
<i>Well, I respectfully disagree.</i>

125
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:59,085
Respect? I don't see no respect.

126
00:06:59,086 --> 00:07:03,005
All I see is a kid
with a $200,000 education

127
00:07:03,006 --> 00:07:07,468
living in my damn house,
playing dumbass video games.
That's what I see.

128
00:07:07,469 --> 00:07:09,388
[clears throat]
<i>You mean Mom's house.</i>

129
00:07:10,305 --> 00:07:11,681
What'd you say?

130
00:07:11,682 --> 00:07:12,974
Come on,
you haven't even cleaned out

131
00:07:12,975 --> 00:07:13,976
her stuff yet.

132
00:07:16,353 --> 00:07:18,771
That's none of
your damn business.

133
00:07:18,772 --> 00:07:20,065
Saved by the bell.

134
00:07:21,275 --> 00:07:23,818
[David] <i>If anyone
should be gaming, it's you.</i>

135
00:07:23,819 --> 00:07:26,864
<i>- Might be good therapy
for all that aggression.</i>
- I'll call you later.

136
00:07:27,614 --> 00:07:28,615
You mine.

137
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:31,034
You mine.

138
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:39,542
You are officially found.

139
00:07:39,543 --> 00:07:41,128
- Bam!
- [automated voice]
<i>That was easy.</i>

140
00:07:42,546 --> 00:07:43,630
Nah, I'm just good.

141
00:07:46,675 --> 00:07:48,260
Let's get my eye in the sky.

142
00:07:50,429 --> 00:07:52,806
Good morning,
my sweet baby drone.

143
00:07:55,184 --> 00:07:56,185
[ringtone playing]

144
00:08:00,230 --> 00:08:01,690
Lord have mercy.

145
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:05,861
<i>There's no James at all?</i>

146
00:08:07,988 --> 00:08:11,199
- Yes, Mark, what is it?
- [laughing] <i>Hey, Pops.</i>

147
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:14,036
"Pops"? I'm not your daddy, man.

148
00:08:14,828 --> 00:08:17,288
<i>Right. Uh... Sorry.</i>

149
00:08:17,289 --> 00:08:20,124
- "Sorry" what?
<i>- Sorry, sir.</i>

150
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:21,709
<i>Um, anyway,
I know you told Faith</i>

151
00:08:21,710 --> 00:08:24,503
<i>you have to work,
but just to tempt you,</i>

152
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:26,839
<i>we're all wearing
these fun shirts to the shower.</i>

153
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:30,426
<i>I, uh, even got
a Grandpa Shark one for you.</i>

154
00:08:30,427 --> 00:08:33,179
[laughing] <i>Look.</i>

155
00:08:33,180 --> 00:08:35,306
<i>He's grumpy, too.</i>

156
00:08:35,307 --> 00:08:37,350
<i>He's got your whiskers
and everything.</i>

157
00:08:37,351 --> 00:08:39,727
- What shower?
<i>- Oh, shit.</i>

158
00:08:39,728 --> 00:08:42,355
<i>Sorry, uh, I guess
I should've talked to Faith</i>

159
00:08:42,356 --> 00:08:44,065
<i>before I made shirts. My bad.</i>

160
00:08:44,066 --> 00:08:46,025
<i>Keep up the good work
over there, okay?</i>

161
00:08:46,026 --> 00:08:48,779
<i>Uh, and thank-thank you
for your service.</i>

162
00:08:51,698 --> 00:08:53,200
[taps key]

163
00:08:54,618 --> 00:08:56,662
[tense music]

164
00:09:14,221 --> 00:09:16,265
[birds chirping]

165
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:33,030
[William] Damn.
Changed her password again.

166
00:09:33,031 --> 00:09:34,324
[chuckles]

167
00:09:52,384 --> 00:09:54,428
[soft music]

168
00:10:03,729 --> 00:10:04,730
Damn.

169
00:10:16,491 --> 00:10:19,036
[messages whooshing]

170
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:44,686
[sighing] Oh, shit.

171
00:10:46,772 --> 00:10:47,939
What an asshole.

172
00:11:07,417 --> 00:11:09,461
- [sighs]
- [computer dings]

173
00:11:43,370 --> 00:11:44,912
[Erika, recorded] <i>Remember
to take out the trash today</i>

174
00:11:44,913 --> 00:11:46,789
<i>and be nice to the kids.</i>

175
00:11:46,790 --> 00:11:48,666
<i>- I love you, baby.</i>
- [William sighs]

176
00:11:48,667 --> 00:11:49,668
Yeah.

177
00:12:06,351 --> 00:12:08,436
- Boom!
- [automated voice]
<i>That was easy.</i>

178
00:12:08,437 --> 00:12:09,895
Say it again.

179
00:12:09,896 --> 00:12:12,022
[automated voice] <i>That was easy.</i>

180
00:12:12,023 --> 00:12:13,358
Damn right.

181
00:12:22,909 --> 00:12:25,661
<i>William. You really took
your time with this one,
didn't you?</i>

182
00:12:25,662 --> 00:12:29,582
Oh, shit. Hold on, hold on.
I got to add Briggs
to this conversation.

183
00:12:29,583 --> 00:12:30,584
<i>All right.</i>

184
00:12:33,462 --> 00:12:36,255
Director Briggs, you have
FBI Special Agent Jeffries

185
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:37,798
- on the line.
<i>- Sir.</i>

186
00:12:37,799 --> 00:12:38,800
<i>Good to meet you, Jeffries.</i>

187
00:12:45,932 --> 00:12:49,226
- Cams are hot.
<i>- All right. Ready here.</i>

188
00:12:49,227 --> 00:12:50,436
<i>Body cam check.</i>

189
00:12:50,437 --> 00:12:52,480
[William] All coming in clear.

190
00:12:52,481 --> 00:12:55,108
<i>- Will, what's the unit number?</i>
- Checking. Stand by.

191
00:12:56,943 --> 00:12:58,694
[Briggs] <i>Listen up, team.</i>

192
00:12:58,695 --> 00:13:00,738
<i>I want this to be clean
and surgical.</i>

193
00:13:00,739 --> 00:13:02,239
<i>We don't know
who these hackers are,</i>

194
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,950
<i>but we know
what they're capable of.</i>

195
00:13:05,285 --> 00:13:07,703
<i>This so-called Disruptor
is trying to reveal</i>

196
00:13:07,704 --> 00:13:09,455
<i>a top secret program
called Goliath,</i>

197
00:13:09,456 --> 00:13:11,582
<i>and that file must not go out.</i>

198
00:13:11,583 --> 00:13:12,917
<i>It's national security.</i>

199
00:13:12,918 --> 00:13:14,376
- [meows]
- [William] Don't worry, sir.

200
00:13:14,377 --> 00:13:16,712
- We're all over this guy.
- [yells]

201
00:13:16,713 --> 00:13:18,548
You little punk.

202
00:13:20,467 --> 00:13:21,468
Touchdown.

203
00:13:23,220 --> 00:13:26,555
Uh, second floor,
east corner, unit 42.

204
00:13:26,556 --> 00:13:28,140
<i>Copy that. Moving in.</i>

205
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:29,809
[indistinct
police radio chatter]

206
00:13:35,023 --> 00:13:37,067
[tense music]

207
00:13:41,696 --> 00:13:43,698
[Jeffries]
<i>All right. Going up the stairs.</i>

208
00:13:46,243 --> 00:13:48,620
[William]
All right, second floor
is clear to proceed.

209
00:13:51,957 --> 00:13:53,333
[thunder crashing]

210
00:13:55,835 --> 00:13:56,836
Ooh!

211
00:14:10,058 --> 00:14:11,559
Guys, you need to hurry.

212
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:14,353
These security cameras
are on public networks.

213
00:14:14,354 --> 00:14:17,189
Disruptor could be watching
our every move.

214
00:14:17,190 --> 00:14:19,108
[Jeffries] <i>Copy that.</i>

215
00:14:19,109 --> 00:14:21,402
- [William] Open door, unit 209.
- [dog barking]

216
00:14:21,403 --> 00:14:24,113
[agent whispering]
<i>Back inside. Lock the door.</i>

217
00:14:24,114 --> 00:14:25,781
[Jeffries] <i>Approaching.</i>

218
00:14:25,782 --> 00:14:27,658
[dog barking]

219
00:14:27,659 --> 00:14:28,660
Here we go.

220
00:14:31,997 --> 00:14:34,124
- [baby crying nearby]
- [agents breathing heavily]

221
00:14:49,639 --> 00:14:52,766
<i>Oh, shit.
It's another one of his decoys.</i>

222
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,602
<i>Clever little bastard.</i>

223
00:14:54,603 --> 00:14:57,438
- [loud whooshing]
<i>- Shit.</i>

224
00:14:57,439 --> 00:14:58,607
<i>What the hell was that?</i>

225
00:15:00,525 --> 00:15:02,526
<i>Jesus, what the hell was that?</i>

226
00:15:02,527 --> 00:15:04,194
[alarms blaring]

227
00:15:04,195 --> 00:15:05,613
[explosion booming]

228
00:15:05,614 --> 00:15:06,698
<i>Will, what was that?</i>

229
00:15:10,577 --> 00:15:11,869
[static crackling]

230
00:15:11,870 --> 00:15:13,079
I'm checking. Stand by.

231
00:15:15,749 --> 00:15:17,709
[whooshing]

232
00:15:23,715 --> 00:15:25,091
[chiming repeatedly]

233
00:15:26,593 --> 00:15:28,595
[alarm siren blaring]

234
00:15:33,433 --> 00:15:35,894
- [indistinct radio chatter]
- [William] Shit.

235
00:15:38,146 --> 00:15:39,813
[phone ringing]

236
00:15:39,814 --> 00:15:41,566
[siren blaring]

237
00:15:43,902 --> 00:15:45,570
[line ringing]

238
00:15:53,495 --> 00:15:55,621
[chiming]

239
00:15:55,622 --> 00:15:57,706
[reporter]
<i>Uh, reports are pouring in...</i>

240
00:15:57,707 --> 00:16:00,084
- Oh, this is insane.
<i>- ...falling debris or meteors,</i>

241
00:16:00,085 --> 00:16:02,753
<i>but we can't tell yet
what exactly is going on.</i>

242
00:16:02,754 --> 00:16:04,463
<i>-It's pandemonium.</i>
- [line ringing]

243
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:06,131
<i>Uh, reports coming in:
fires in Dodger Stadium.</i>

244
00:16:06,132 --> 00:16:07,800
- [William] Shit.
- [reporter] <i>Uh, a Century City</i>

245
00:16:07,801 --> 00:16:09,301
<i>building has collapsed.</i>

246
00:16:09,302 --> 00:16:10,928
<i>...supposed to break up
and burn up</i>

247
00:16:10,929 --> 00:16:12,638
<i>upon entering
Earth's atmosphere,</i>

248
00:16:12,639 --> 00:16:15,099
<i>becoming what used to be
called shooting stars.</i>

249
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:17,935
- [whooshing, rumbling]
- [William] Oh.

250
00:16:17,936 --> 00:16:19,561
Jesus.

251
00:16:19,562 --> 00:16:21,146
[frantic crowd chatter]

252
00:16:21,147 --> 00:16:23,274
- Oh!
- [people screaming]

253
00:16:24,526 --> 00:16:25,944
[phone ringing]

254
00:16:29,781 --> 00:16:31,950
[reporter speaking Spanish]

255
00:16:39,416 --> 00:16:41,084
[phone ringing]

256
00:16:48,508 --> 00:16:50,552
[phone stops ringing]

257
00:16:54,639 --> 00:16:57,558
<i>Some are speeding up.
Some are slowing down.</i>

258
00:16:57,559 --> 00:16:59,518
<i>This scatters
their entry points</i>

259
00:16:59,519 --> 00:17:01,520
<i>across the hemisphere,
maybe even wider.</i>

260
00:17:01,521 --> 00:17:03,647
<i>Your location is gonna get hit.</i>

261
00:17:03,648 --> 00:17:05,442
<i>I'm heading to one
of the crash sites now.</i>

262
00:17:06,484 --> 00:17:07,485
[phones ringing]

263
00:17:12,699 --> 00:17:15,284
[whooshing]

264
00:17:15,285 --> 00:17:17,578
- [clattering, rumbling]
- Shit!

265
00:17:17,579 --> 00:17:19,038
Whoa!

266
00:17:24,419 --> 00:17:25,754
[phone ringing]

267
00:17:30,383 --> 00:17:32,010
[line ringing]

268
00:17:36,598 --> 00:17:38,767
[William]
Come on, come on. Pick up.

269
00:17:51,654 --> 00:17:53,698
[tense music]

270
00:18:04,834 --> 00:18:06,669
Come on. Where are you?

271
00:18:14,969 --> 00:18:17,013
[clattering, rumbling]

272
00:18:18,389 --> 00:18:21,476
Got you.
Okay. Just sit tight, baby.

273
00:18:25,730 --> 00:18:28,023
[reporter] <i>FEMA has instructed
all citizens</i>

274
00:18:28,024 --> 00:18:30,442
<i>to take shelter immediately
on the ground.</i>

275
00:18:30,443 --> 00:18:32,361
<i>Basements, parking garages,</i>

276
00:18:32,362 --> 00:18:34,154
<i>fallout shelters,
anything that can provide</i>

277
00:18:34,155 --> 00:18:36,240
<i>safe and effective coverage</i>

278
00:18:36,241 --> 00:18:38,659
<i>until the meteor storm
has stopped.</i>

279
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:40,661
<i>We have no other information
at this point,</i>

280
00:18:40,662 --> 00:18:42,371
<i>-but world government leaders</i>
- [line ringing]

281
00:18:42,372 --> 00:18:44,248
<i>are engaging to determine
the amount of damage</i>

282
00:18:44,249 --> 00:18:47,126
<i>-and casualties so far.</i>
- [William] Come on! Come on!

283
00:18:50,046 --> 00:18:51,588
<i>- Hey, Dad.</i>
- [sirens blaring]

284
00:18:51,589 --> 00:18:53,131
<i>- Dad, Dad, you seeing this?</i>
- [whooshing]

285
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:54,758
<i>- Are you seeing this? Oh, my...</i>
- Dave.

286
00:18:54,759 --> 00:18:56,176
- Listen to me.
- [David breathing heavily]

287
00:18:56,177 --> 00:18:57,845
- Get out of there now.
- [phone clatters]

288
00:18:57,846 --> 00:18:59,556
- Dave!
- [grunting]

289
00:19:01,182 --> 00:19:03,767
No, no, no! You got to get up!

290
00:19:03,768 --> 00:19:05,394
Keep running!

291
00:19:05,395 --> 00:19:07,896
[David] <i>What? I can't hear you.</i>

292
00:19:07,897 --> 00:19:09,273
[explosion booming]

293
00:19:09,274 --> 00:19:11,233
[David breathing heavily]

294
00:19:11,234 --> 00:19:12,985
[William]
You got to go left now!

295
00:19:12,986 --> 00:19:15,320
- And run, boy!
<i>- Dad, Dad.</i>

296
00:19:15,321 --> 00:19:17,072
[William]
Make a right now at the corner!

297
00:19:17,073 --> 00:19:19,575
- [David] <i>Holy shit.</i>
- Dave!

298
00:19:19,576 --> 00:19:21,785
<i>- I'm okay. I'm okay.</i>
- Go.

299
00:19:21,786 --> 00:19:24,121
- Go!
- [heavy breathing continues]

300
00:19:24,122 --> 00:19:27,207
[loud electronic humming]

301
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:29,460
[static droning]

302
00:19:34,591 --> 00:19:37,218
Come on, come on. Come on, Dave.

303
00:19:40,722 --> 00:19:41,723
Come on.

304
00:19:43,850 --> 00:19:45,225
Thank God.

305
00:19:45,226 --> 00:19:46,561
[sighs]

306
00:19:49,731 --> 00:19:50,732
[sighs]

307
00:19:55,778 --> 00:19:57,362
[Crystal] <i>President is safe,</i>

308
00:19:57,363 --> 00:19:59,031
<i>location undisclosed.</i>

309
00:19:59,032 --> 00:20:01,867
<i>VP, justices, chiefs of staff
all secure.</i>

310
00:20:01,868 --> 00:20:04,161
[Briggs]
<i>Okay. We have DHS joining,</i>

311
00:20:04,162 --> 00:20:06,079
<i>and we have NASA on the ground
at an event site.</i>

312
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:07,457
<i>Dr. Salas,
what do you see in there?</i>

313
00:20:09,626 --> 00:20:10,627
<i>Wow.</i>

314
00:20:16,424 --> 00:20:17,591
Whoa.

315
00:20:17,592 --> 00:20:18,593
[Sandra] <i>Oh, my God.</i>

316
00:20:19,886 --> 00:20:21,261
<i>This is incredible.</i>

317
00:20:21,262 --> 00:20:23,221
<i>I'm gonna get closer.</i>

318
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:25,308
[grunting]

319
00:20:27,101 --> 00:20:30,187
<i>It's huge. It's got to be
like 30, 40 feet.</i>

320
00:20:30,188 --> 00:20:32,064
<i>With this size and shape,
they should've shattered.</i>

321
00:20:32,065 --> 00:20:34,024
<i>Can you tell yet
what they're comprised of?</i>

322
00:20:34,025 --> 00:20:36,360
<i>No, sir, I've never seen
anything like this.</i>

323
00:20:36,361 --> 00:20:37,903
- [heavy rumbling]
- [William] Whoa!

324
00:20:37,904 --> 00:20:39,613
<i>- What was that?
- Stand by.</i>

325
00:20:39,614 --> 00:20:41,531
[Crystal]
<i>What the hell was that?</i>

326
00:20:41,532 --> 00:20:42,991
- [Sandra speaking indistinctly
through static]
- Stand by.

327
00:20:42,992 --> 00:20:45,411
I'm rerouting her cell
to our satellite.

328
00:20:52,418 --> 00:20:54,544
[Sandra]
<i>Wow. This is incredible.</i>

329
00:20:54,545 --> 00:20:57,464
<i>It's, uh... it's freezing cold.
It's, um...</i>

330
00:20:57,465 --> 00:20:59,049
<i>Oh, my God!</i>

331
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:00,509
- Get away!
<i>- Oh, my God!</i>

332
00:21:00,510 --> 00:21:01,970
[Sandra grunts]

333
00:21:02,971 --> 00:21:04,680
<i>What the hell is that?</i>

334
00:21:04,681 --> 00:21:06,140
[Sandra gasping]

335
00:21:08,726 --> 00:21:10,102
Sandra!

336
00:21:10,103 --> 00:21:11,104
Sa...

337
00:21:12,605 --> 00:21:14,856
<i>Secretary Crystal, the protocol
is DEFCON here, yes?</i>

338
00:21:14,857 --> 00:21:17,234
<i>Absolutely.
Authorizing DEFCON now.</i>

339
00:21:17,235 --> 00:21:19,528
<i>I'll notify the president.</i>

340
00:21:19,529 --> 00:21:21,196
[Briggs]
<i>Prioritize all armed assets</i>

341
00:21:21,197 --> 00:21:23,323
<i>to domestic meteor sites
immediately.</i>

342
00:21:23,324 --> 00:21:25,283
<i>We need to contain
whatever the hell that was.</i>

343
00:21:25,284 --> 00:21:26,702
<i>I'm talking
full mobilization here.</i>

344
00:21:26,703 --> 00:21:28,120
[General Austin] <i>We're on it.</i>

345
00:21:28,121 --> 00:21:29,871
[William]
Come on, come on, come on.

346
00:21:29,872 --> 00:21:31,999
[Briggs] <i>General Austin,
if this is happening worldwide,</i>

347
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:33,625
<i>we'll need to sync up
immediately
to coordinate intel.</i>

348
00:21:33,626 --> 00:21:35,627
<i>Reach out to the UN,
NATO, everyone.</i>

349
00:21:35,628 --> 00:21:38,255
Nothing short
of a planetary alliance.

350
00:21:38,256 --> 00:21:39,840
[Austin] <i>I'm calling
for an urgent meeting</i>

351
00:21:39,841 --> 00:21:41,591
<i>with the UN General Assembly
right now.</i>

352
00:21:41,592 --> 00:21:42,926
[Briggs] <i>Crystal,
once the president is secure,</i>

353
00:21:42,927 --> 00:21:44,469
<i>brief him on what you saw.</i>

354
00:21:44,470 --> 00:21:45,762
<i>He's gonna need
to make a statement,</i>

355
00:21:45,763 --> 00:21:47,264
<i>declare a state of emergency.</i>

356
00:21:47,265 --> 00:21:49,016
[Crystal] <i>Absolutely.</i>

357
00:21:49,017 --> 00:21:50,767
[Briggs] <i>Will, you're
my eyes and ears on this.</i>

358
00:21:50,768 --> 00:21:53,562
<i>I need your domestic threat
analysis right away.</i>

359
00:21:53,563 --> 00:21:54,772
[William] Roger that.

360
00:22:05,283 --> 00:22:08,410
<i>Radford. What are the rules
of engagement here?</i>

361
00:22:08,411 --> 00:22:10,912
Engagement? Shit if I know.

362
00:22:10,913 --> 00:22:12,248
Don't do nothing.

363
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:15,334
[Jeffries]
<i>What the hell is that?</i>

364
00:22:16,836 --> 00:22:19,212
That thing is huge.

365
00:22:19,213 --> 00:22:21,424
- [rumbling steps]
- [mechanical whirring]

366
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:24,385
[mouthing]

367
00:22:27,055 --> 00:22:28,513
[William] Whoa.

368
00:22:28,514 --> 00:22:29,974
Can't believe this shit.

369
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:44,362
Goddamn.

370
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:45,822
[Jeffries] <i>Oh, my God.</i>

371
00:22:45,823 --> 00:22:48,366
[panicked breathing]

372
00:22:48,367 --> 00:22:49,910
<i>What the hell is that, Will?</i>

373
00:22:49,911 --> 00:22:51,579
[phone ringing]

374
00:22:53,790 --> 00:22:57,376
Oh... my... God.

375
00:22:58,544 --> 00:23:00,671
- [horns honking]
- [panicked chatter]

376
00:23:03,132 --> 00:23:04,592
[ringtone playing]

377
00:23:05,885 --> 00:23:07,887
Sit tight.
I'm coming back to you.

378
00:23:09,555 --> 00:23:13,225
- How you doing? You all right?
<i>- I figured this would be
a safe place to talk.</i>

379
00:23:13,226 --> 00:23:15,519
Listen, I need you to get
to your sister right now.

380
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:17,646
<i>Nah, Dad, Dad,
I-I spoke to her. She's safe.</i>

381
00:23:17,647 --> 00:23:19,564
<i>Mark's picking her up.</i>

382
00:23:19,565 --> 00:23:21,108
<i>Listen, I need to talk to you
about something I stumbled on.</i>

383
00:23:21,109 --> 00:23:22,651
I don't have time
for that right now, okay?

384
00:23:22,652 --> 00:23:24,569
<i>- Dad! This is important.</i>
- [computer chimes]

385
00:23:24,570 --> 00:23:27,239
<i>I don't think you understand
the dynamics at play here.</i>

386
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:29,908
Nobody understands, okay?
We're in a national crisis here.

387
00:23:29,909 --> 00:23:32,035
<i>Goddamn it, Dad, I do.</i>

388
00:23:32,036 --> 00:23:34,371
<i>I have information
I think you might want to know.</i>

389
00:23:34,372 --> 00:23:37,249
Not now, Dave. Not now.

390
00:23:37,250 --> 00:23:40,127
I need you to stay sheltered
and sit tight.

391
00:23:40,128 --> 00:23:41,962
<i>- Will.</i>
- I'm here.

392
00:23:41,963 --> 00:23:43,588
<i>They're not doing anything.
This doesn't feel right.</i>

393
00:23:43,589 --> 00:23:45,799
[William] Just hold tight,
hold tight, hold tight.

394
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:48,718
- Oh!
- [loud electronic humming]

395
00:23:48,719 --> 00:23:50,763
[screaming]

396
00:23:55,351 --> 00:23:57,644
[explosive whooshing]

397
00:23:57,645 --> 00:23:59,813
Oh. Run!

398
00:23:59,814 --> 00:24:00,981
[Jeffries gasping]

399
00:24:00,982 --> 00:24:02,191
[William] Get out of there!

400
00:24:08,406 --> 00:24:10,825
[loud whirring, rumbling]

401
00:24:12,660 --> 00:24:15,203
No! No!

402
00:24:15,204 --> 00:24:16,788
Sheila!

403
00:24:16,789 --> 00:24:19,167
[alarm siren blaring]

404
00:24:22,587 --> 00:24:24,462
Oh, my God.

405
00:24:24,463 --> 00:24:26,756
[reporter] <i>Uh,
eyewitness video is coming in</i>

406
00:24:26,757 --> 00:24:30,177
<i>from all over the world
of terrifying machines</i>

407
00:24:30,178 --> 00:24:32,179
<i>rising out of these meteors.</i>

408
00:24:32,180 --> 00:24:35,056
<i>Citizens are astonished
by what is happening.</i>

409
00:24:35,057 --> 00:24:37,601
<i>Destruction and chaos
is rampant worldwide.</i>

410
00:24:37,602 --> 00:24:39,644
<i>Now, as far as we know,</i>

411
00:24:39,645 --> 00:24:41,855
<i>governments
have not yet determined</i>

412
00:24:41,856 --> 00:24:45,275
<i>what these things are
and what their response
will be.</i>

413
00:24:45,276 --> 00:24:46,776
Damn.

414
00:24:46,777 --> 00:24:48,236
[reporter] <i>Space Force, NASA,</i>

415
00:24:48,237 --> 00:24:49,863
<i>and the UAP Task Force</i>

416
00:24:49,864 --> 00:24:52,199
<i>are headed to event sites
right now.</i>

417
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:54,284
<i>We've been instructed
to announce</i>

418
00:24:54,285 --> 00:24:57,495
<i>that people of the world
should shelter in place.</i>

419
00:24:57,496 --> 00:25:00,166
<i>Absolutely do not go outside.</i>

420
00:25:01,125 --> 00:25:03,169
[alarm siren continues blaring]

421
00:25:13,137 --> 00:25:14,931
[heavy rumbling]

422
00:25:21,354 --> 00:25:23,355
[reporter]
<i>Destruction is widespread</i>

423
00:25:23,356 --> 00:25:25,273
<i>as these machines
make their way</i>

424
00:25:25,274 --> 00:25:28,109
<i>through cities,
towns and rural areas,</i>

425
00:25:28,110 --> 00:25:30,487
<i>annihilating critical infrastructure,</i>

426
00:25:30,488 --> 00:25:32,697
<i>resources, military bases</i>

427
00:25:32,698 --> 00:25:35,576
<i>and communication centers
across the world.</i>

428
00:25:37,870 --> 00:25:39,913
<i>We've been told
from Space Force</i>

429
00:25:39,914 --> 00:25:42,457
<i>that the violent storms
around the world</i>

430
00:25:42,458 --> 00:25:45,586
<i>were caused by the massive
atmospheric disruption...</i>

431
00:25:48,673 --> 00:25:51,383
<i>...from thousands of meteors
burning through</i>

432
00:25:51,384 --> 00:25:53,260
<i>the Earth's ozone
at the same time.</i>

433
00:25:53,261 --> 00:25:55,513
<i>This attack was
clearly organized...</i>

434
00:25:57,265 --> 00:25:59,975
<i>...and coordinated
by an intelligent force,</i>

435
00:25:59,976 --> 00:26:04,271
<i>and the storm should have been
an immediate emergency,</i>

436
00:26:04,272 --> 00:26:05,982
<i>but all satellites
were blinded...</i>

437
00:26:09,235 --> 00:26:11,861
<i>...and no one on Earth
could see what was coming.</i>

438
00:26:11,862 --> 00:26:13,697
[ringtone playing]

439
00:26:13,698 --> 00:26:15,616
<i>We'll have more information
on satellites soon.</i>

440
00:26:16,701 --> 00:26:17,826
[panting]

441
00:26:17,827 --> 00:26:20,328
<i>Mark never showed, Dad.</i>

442
00:26:20,329 --> 00:26:22,831
What are you doing outside?

443
00:26:22,832 --> 00:26:24,583
<i>- Dad.</i>
- [loud electronic humming]

444
00:26:25,710 --> 00:26:28,169
Get away from that! Okay?

445
00:26:28,170 --> 00:26:29,922
Stay clear of that stuff!

446
00:26:30,965 --> 00:26:33,425
Hey! Hey! Get out of there!

447
00:26:33,426 --> 00:26:34,468
Go!

448
00:26:35,803 --> 00:26:36,804
Run!

449
00:26:37,638 --> 00:26:39,640
Go! Faith!

450
00:26:45,313 --> 00:26:47,230
[Faith] <i>Oh, shit! Shit!</i>

451
00:26:47,231 --> 00:26:49,483
<i>- Dad! Dad!</i>
- Faith!

452
00:26:50,568 --> 00:26:52,987
[crashing, metallic screeching]

453
00:26:57,742 --> 00:27:00,368
[alarm siren blaring]

454
00:27:00,369 --> 00:27:03,205
[mechanical whirring]

455
00:27:06,876 --> 00:27:07,877
Faith.

456
00:27:09,545 --> 00:27:12,255
- [loud electronic humming]
- Faith!

457
00:27:12,256 --> 00:27:13,966
Faith!

458
00:27:15,968 --> 00:27:17,678
[heartbeat thumping]

459
00:27:19,722 --> 00:27:22,224
[sighs] Are you okay?

460
00:27:24,560 --> 00:27:26,269
Are you okay?

461
00:27:26,270 --> 00:27:28,271
[Faith breathing heavily]

462
00:27:28,272 --> 00:27:30,316
[rustling]

463
00:27:31,859 --> 00:27:33,694
[gasping]

464
00:27:38,532 --> 00:27:39,949
Come on. Okay.

465
00:27:39,950 --> 00:27:41,409
Look.

466
00:27:41,410 --> 00:27:43,828
How... how are you?
How's the baby?

467
00:27:43,829 --> 00:27:45,955
<i>Oh, my God, it hurts so bad.</i>

468
00:27:45,956 --> 00:27:47,374
[William] Okay, stay calm.

469
00:27:47,375 --> 00:27:49,084
Stay calm.

470
00:27:49,085 --> 00:27:50,835
Your heart rate is way too high.

471
00:27:50,836 --> 00:27:52,922
- Don't you move, okay?
- [pained whimper]

472
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,883
[Faith breathing heavily]

473
00:27:56,884 --> 00:27:59,427
[line ringing]

474
00:27:59,428 --> 00:28:01,262
[automated voice]
<i>All operators are busy now.</i>

475
00:28:01,263 --> 00:28:02,514
<i>Please try
your call another time.</i>

476
00:28:02,515 --> 00:28:04,391
I'm coming!
I'm coming for you now!

477
00:28:04,392 --> 00:28:05,767
Okay?

478
00:28:05,768 --> 00:28:07,602
Here I come!

479
00:28:07,603 --> 00:28:09,479
[whimpers, groans]

480
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:11,649
[William]
Damn it! We're in lockdown.

481
00:28:16,362 --> 00:28:18,489
[tapping keys]

482
00:28:19,490 --> 00:28:20,824
[automated voice]
<i>Access denied.</i>

483
00:28:20,825 --> 00:28:22,450
[William] Damn it.

484
00:28:22,451 --> 00:28:24,452
[pained whimpering]

485
00:28:24,453 --> 00:28:26,955
[Faith groaning]

486
00:28:26,956 --> 00:28:28,706
- Okay.
<i>- Access granted.</i>

487
00:28:28,707 --> 00:28:29,874
Okay.

488
00:28:29,875 --> 00:28:31,418
Okay, I'm coming.

489
00:28:31,419 --> 00:28:32,420
I'm coming right now.

490
00:28:36,757 --> 00:28:38,842
Okay. I'm coming to you.

491
00:28:38,843 --> 00:28:40,636
- I'm coming to you.
<i>- Dad.</i>

492
00:28:42,430 --> 00:28:44,097
- [Faith groans]
- Okay.

493
00:28:44,098 --> 00:28:45,557
I got to take the steps.

494
00:28:45,558 --> 00:28:47,393
<i>- What happened?</i>
- Has to be DEFCON 1.

495
00:28:48,227 --> 00:28:51,521
All essential buildings secured.

496
00:28:51,522 --> 00:28:54,190
- The irony, right, Dad?
- [doorknob rattles]

497
00:28:54,191 --> 00:28:55,608
[automated voice]
<i>Access denied.</i>

498
00:28:55,609 --> 00:28:57,444
- Come on! Come on!
- [doorknob rattling]

499
00:28:57,445 --> 00:28:59,028
Son of a bitch!

500
00:28:59,029 --> 00:29:01,322
<i>You never want to
leave that place.</i>

501
00:29:01,323 --> 00:29:03,366
- [William grunts]
<i>- And now
it won't let you leave.</i>

502
00:29:03,367 --> 00:29:04,909
Don't worry.

503
00:29:04,910 --> 00:29:07,328
I'm gonna figure something out, honey.

504
00:29:07,329 --> 00:29:09,205
I'm gonna figure something out.

505
00:29:09,206 --> 00:29:12,042
- I'm sorry, but I'm coming.
- [Faith groaning, sobbing]

506
00:29:14,253 --> 00:29:16,297
[somber music]

507
00:29:19,592 --> 00:29:22,093
[Faith breathing heavily,
whimpering]

508
00:29:22,094 --> 00:29:24,721
- Dad, it hurts so bad.
- Okay, okay.

509
00:29:24,722 --> 00:29:27,140
Stay calm. Stay calm.

510
00:29:27,141 --> 00:29:28,725
[Faith]
<i>I got to get to shelter.</i>

511
00:29:28,726 --> 00:29:30,351
<i>My office is only a mile away.</i>

512
00:29:30,352 --> 00:29:32,103
<i>- I can make it.</i>
- No. No.

513
00:29:32,104 --> 00:29:33,105
Stay where you are.

514
00:29:34,607 --> 00:29:35,858
I'm-a get you out of there.

515
00:29:38,736 --> 00:29:40,278
[heavy thudding]

516
00:29:40,279 --> 00:29:42,155
<i>Dad, what's that sound?</i>

517
00:29:42,156 --> 00:29:44,699
[William] Shit! It's close by.

518
00:29:44,700 --> 00:29:46,701
[heavy thudding continues]

519
00:29:46,702 --> 00:29:49,162
[Faith breathing heavily]

520
00:29:49,163 --> 00:29:51,039
[Faith whimpers]

521
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:52,500
Look, I'm getting you
out of there. Just hold tight.

522
00:29:54,793 --> 00:29:57,629
You see that Tesla
in front of you?

523
00:29:57,630 --> 00:30:00,548
- I need you to get to it.
<i>- Dad, I can't drive like this.</i>

524
00:30:00,549 --> 00:30:02,968
Don't worry. I got you.

525
00:30:08,182 --> 00:30:09,641
Quick as you can.

526
00:30:09,642 --> 00:30:11,893
I'll open it for you.

527
00:30:11,894 --> 00:30:14,103
Hurry up, baby. Come on, Faith.

528
00:30:14,104 --> 00:30:15,939
[loud electronic humming]

529
00:30:15,940 --> 00:30:17,441
Hurry, hurry.

530
00:30:18,817 --> 00:30:20,694
A little faster, honey.
I know it hurts.

531
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:26,283
[loud electronic humming]

532
00:30:28,452 --> 00:30:30,621
Okay, I'm getting you out
of there right now. Hold tight.

533
00:30:32,122 --> 00:30:34,625
[electric motor whirring]

534
00:30:37,586 --> 00:30:39,630
[loud electronic humming]

535
00:30:43,342 --> 00:30:44,635
Man, that was close.

536
00:30:45,678 --> 00:30:50,057
Faith. Listen to me. I got you.

537
00:30:51,058 --> 00:30:52,518
- I got you.
<i>- Okay.</i>

538
00:30:53,519 --> 00:30:55,937
[sirens wailing]

539
00:30:55,938 --> 00:30:57,605
- [rapid beeping]
- All right.

540
00:30:57,606 --> 00:31:00,650
[Faith shuddering]

541
00:31:00,651 --> 00:31:03,027
[William]
Hospitals are full, baby,

542
00:31:03,028 --> 00:31:04,737
but don't worry.

543
00:31:04,738 --> 00:31:07,282
I'm gonna get you
to a secure location.

544
00:31:07,283 --> 00:31:08,992
[automated voice]
<i>Your destination</i>

545
00:31:08,993 --> 00:31:11,202
<i>- is one mile away.
- Oh, my God.</i>

546
00:31:11,203 --> 00:31:12,787
<i>There's so much destruction.</i>

547
00:31:12,788 --> 00:31:14,289
[William]
Don't look at that, sweetheart.

548
00:31:14,290 --> 00:31:17,292
Just keep your eyes on me.
Just focus on me.

549
00:31:17,293 --> 00:31:19,628
[pained, shaky breathing]

550
00:31:20,963 --> 00:31:21,964
[Faith] <i>Okay.</i>

551
00:31:23,465 --> 00:31:25,717
[William] All right, I got you.

552
00:31:25,718 --> 00:31:27,303
I got everything under control.

553
00:31:36,979 --> 00:31:37,980
Hey.

554
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:42,568
I don't blame you for not
wanting me at your shower.

555
00:31:44,737 --> 00:31:47,990
<i>Now? We have to do this now?</i>

556
00:31:49,950 --> 00:31:50,951
No.

557
00:31:51,785 --> 00:31:54,329
I'm serious. I mean...

558
00:31:54,330 --> 00:31:56,998
I put you and your brother
through a lot of pain.

559
00:31:56,999 --> 00:31:58,250
<i>Jesus, Dad.</i>

560
00:31:59,668 --> 00:32:01,295
<i>Do you know
what your problem is?</i>

561
00:32:03,005 --> 00:32:06,008
<i>You think you have more power
than you really do.</i>

562
00:32:07,343 --> 00:32:11,095
<i>You think you had the power to
have saved Mom from a disease.</i>

563
00:32:11,096 --> 00:32:13,849
<i>You think you have
the power to make me happy.</i>

564
00:32:15,017 --> 00:32:17,977
<i>You think you have the power
to keep the world safe.</i>

565
00:32:17,978 --> 00:32:19,520
<i>You got to wake up.</i>

566
00:32:19,521 --> 00:32:21,981
<i>You don't have any power.</i>

567
00:32:21,982 --> 00:32:23,316
<i>None.</i>

568
00:32:23,317 --> 00:32:24,901
<i>You got to let go.</i>

569
00:32:24,902 --> 00:32:26,403
<i>I'm not a kid anymore.</i>

570
00:32:28,030 --> 00:32:29,948
[Faith whimpering, shuddering]

571
00:32:55,391 --> 00:32:57,184
[phone dings]

572
00:33:07,277 --> 00:33:08,278
Okay.

573
00:33:17,746 --> 00:33:19,665
[sighs]

574
00:33:20,958 --> 00:33:21,959
All right.

575
00:33:24,670 --> 00:33:26,422
[scoffs]

576
00:33:32,678 --> 00:33:34,929
[automated voice] <i>Turn right.</i>

577
00:33:34,930 --> 00:33:37,307
Come on, come on, come on,
come on, come on, come on.

578
00:33:56,827 --> 00:33:58,954
[dramatic music]

579
00:33:59,913 --> 00:34:00,914
[computer clicks]

580
00:34:10,257 --> 00:34:11,924
- Mark, Mark, can you hear me?
<i>- What?</i>

581
00:34:11,925 --> 00:34:13,552
- Mark.
<i>- Who is that?</i>

582
00:34:14,595 --> 00:34:16,721
It's me, Will.
Faith is in trouble.

583
00:34:16,722 --> 00:34:18,264
<i>What?</i>

584
00:34:18,265 --> 00:34:20,516
- She's injured.
<i>- No, uh, uh, sh...</i>

585
00:34:20,517 --> 00:34:22,685
<i>My-my phone's
been frizzing out.
I-I'm on my way to her now.</i>

586
00:34:22,686 --> 00:34:25,772
Mark, you listen closely.
Faith is losing blood.

587
00:34:25,773 --> 00:34:28,608
Now, you get your skinny ass
over there now.

588
00:34:28,609 --> 00:34:29,860
<i>I'm on my way to her right now.</i>

589
00:34:41,622 --> 00:34:43,539
[somber music]

590
00:34:43,540 --> 00:34:44,541
[sighs]

591
00:35:15,614 --> 00:35:17,740
[computer chiming]

592
00:35:17,741 --> 00:35:19,993
[William] Oh, thank God.

593
00:35:21,662 --> 00:35:22,871
Wait. What?

594
00:35:25,624 --> 00:35:27,375
[reporter]
<i>A delayed report just came in</i>

595
00:35:27,376 --> 00:35:29,418
<i>from the International
Space Station,</i>

596
00:35:29,419 --> 00:35:32,797
<i>confirming the violent storms
the world experienced</i>

597
00:35:32,798 --> 00:35:36,384
<i>were from thousands
of meteors blasting
through the atmosphere.</i>

598
00:35:36,385 --> 00:35:38,469
<i>Meteors were
intentionally crashed</i>

599
00:35:38,470 --> 00:35:40,304
<i>into hundreds of satellites...</i>

600
00:35:40,305 --> 00:35:43,015
- [glass shatters]
- [static crackling]

601
00:35:43,016 --> 00:35:45,018
<i>...to obliterate
any chance of a warning.</i>

602
00:35:50,315 --> 00:35:54,277
<i>Also, military assets worldwide
are assembled to strike back.</i>

603
00:35:54,278 --> 00:35:58,489
<i>We're told the U.S. president
is being briefed
any minute now.</i>

604
00:35:58,490 --> 00:36:02,034
<i>Attack squadrons of F-35s
and Black Hawks are on standby</i>

605
00:36:02,035 --> 00:36:04,495
<i>to launch hundreds of sorties</i>

606
00:36:04,496 --> 00:36:06,330
<i>while AWACS are taking off now</i>

607
00:36:06,331 --> 00:36:08,875
<i>to identify priority
strike targets.</i>

608
00:36:08,876 --> 00:36:14,213
<i>Chinooks and C-130s
are dropping
airborne troops to engage</i>

609
00:36:14,214 --> 00:36:17,091
<i>once the presidential order
has been given.</i>

610
00:36:17,092 --> 00:36:19,594
<i>Ground troops are making
their way to the front lines.</i>

611
00:36:19,595 --> 00:36:22,346
<i>Tank battalions
are positioning in cities</i>

612
00:36:22,347 --> 00:36:24,765
<i>while the Norfolk naval fleet
is closing in.</i>

613
00:36:24,766 --> 00:36:25,809
[computer chimes]

614
00:36:29,479 --> 00:36:31,856
[Austin] <i>They have wiped out
our entire satellite network,</i>

615
00:36:31,857 --> 00:36:34,859
<i>and we have no intel
on our sensitive locations.</i>

616
00:36:34,860 --> 00:36:36,986
[Briggs] <i>I had DHS
terror analyst Will Radford</i>

617
00:36:36,987 --> 00:36:38,446
<i>prepare the threat report.</i>

618
00:36:38,447 --> 00:36:39,989
<i>Will, what are
the high-priority,</i>

619
00:36:39,990 --> 00:36:41,991
<i>most vulnerable sites?</i>

620
00:36:41,992 --> 00:36:43,784
[William]
Mr. President, gentlemen,

621
00:36:43,785 --> 00:36:46,996
we're seeing a full attack
on our infrastructure:

622
00:36:46,997 --> 00:36:49,707
on power grids, water,
communication

623
00:36:49,708 --> 00:36:52,501
and top-level military targets.

624
00:36:52,502 --> 00:36:54,170
They knew exactly
where they were going,

625
00:36:54,171 --> 00:36:57,256
and they are systematically
eliminating resources

626
00:36:57,257 --> 00:37:00,468
and our ability
to coordinate a response.

627
00:37:00,469 --> 00:37:02,219
Here, let me show you.

628
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:05,723
These locations are our
global response headquarters,

629
00:37:05,724 --> 00:37:07,516
our most sensitive targets,

630
00:37:07,517 --> 00:37:09,811
and they're taking them out
one by one.

631
00:37:11,355 --> 00:37:14,106
Based on their
prioritized destruction

632
00:37:14,107 --> 00:37:17,526
of these critical
intelligence command centers,

633
00:37:17,527 --> 00:37:19,320
my analysis suggests

634
00:37:19,321 --> 00:37:22,531
nuclear power facilities
are next.

635
00:37:22,532 --> 00:37:26,118
Electric grids will follow,
leaving us completely helpless.

636
00:37:26,119 --> 00:37:27,828
[Briggs] <i>Do you see that?</i>

637
00:37:27,829 --> 00:37:29,372
<i>They're grouping
to concentrate their attack.</i>

638
00:37:29,373 --> 00:37:30,790
[William] Exactly.

639
00:37:30,791 --> 00:37:33,751
And they will be
much stronger in groups,

640
00:37:33,752 --> 00:37:36,796
so if we concentrate
our armed response assets

641
00:37:36,797 --> 00:37:40,967
to our high-priority locations,
we can hit as many as possible.

642
00:37:40,968 --> 00:37:44,096
I think it's the only option
we have right now.

643
00:37:45,347 --> 00:37:48,767
[Briggs]
<i>Our forces are positioned
and ready to engage right now.</i>

644
00:37:50,727 --> 00:37:51,937
[Briggs] <i>What do you think,
Mr. President?</i>

645
00:37:54,690 --> 00:37:57,566
<i>This plan is
humanity's last stand.</i>

646
00:37:57,567 --> 00:38:00,111
<i>I see no other option
but to initiate</i>

647
00:38:00,112 --> 00:38:02,072
<i>this war of the worlds
to save us all.</i>

648
00:38:13,083 --> 00:38:15,960
[reporter 1]
<i>NATO, China</i> , <i>and the U.S.</i>

649
00:38:15,961 --> 00:38:18,337
<i>have joined forces in what is</i>

650
00:38:18,338 --> 00:38:22,258
<i>an unprecedented collaboration
to defend our cities,</i>

651
00:38:22,259 --> 00:38:25,678
<i>our countries, our way of life.</i>

652
00:38:25,679 --> 00:38:28,347
<i>The world's governments
have finally</i>

653
00:38:28,348 --> 00:38:31,142
<i>put aside their differences
in an effort to protect</i>

654
00:38:31,143 --> 00:38:33,144
<i>the home planet.</i>

655
00:38:33,145 --> 00:38:36,063
[reporter 2] <i>CNN reporting
a breaking live update.</i>

656
00:38:36,064 --> 00:38:38,357
<i>The United States president
is calling</i>

657
00:38:38,358 --> 00:38:40,568
<i>the global military response
a "war of the worlds"</i>

658
00:38:40,569 --> 00:38:42,987
<i>-to save humanity.</i>
- [soldier] <i>Go, go, go, go, go!</i>

659
00:38:42,988 --> 00:38:44,864
[reporter 2]
<i>Air, sea and land forces</i>

660
00:38:44,865 --> 00:38:47,450
<i>have been activated worldwide</i>

661
00:38:47,451 --> 00:38:49,535
<i>to confront these invaders
directly.</i>

662
00:38:49,536 --> 00:38:51,412
<i>Victories and defeats
are unpredictable...</i>

663
00:38:51,413 --> 00:38:54,582
- That's a lot.
<i>- ...but casualties are certain.</i>

664
00:38:54,583 --> 00:38:56,710
Got him! Got him!

665
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,922
[heavy gunfire]

666
00:39:01,923 --> 00:39:03,799
[action music]

667
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:05,552
[William] Whoo! Hell yeah.

668
00:39:06,511 --> 00:39:08,471
[reporter 2] <i>No one knows
if our weapons will be able</i>

669
00:39:08,472 --> 00:39:11,974
<i>to deter their advancement,
but global forces are unloading</i>

670
00:39:11,975 --> 00:39:14,477
<i>everything they have right now.</i>

671
00:39:14,478 --> 00:39:16,270
[William]
Took your ass out, huh?

672
00:39:16,271 --> 00:39:17,897
[soldier] <i>These guys threaten
our way of life,</i>

673
00:39:17,898 --> 00:39:18,732
<i>we're gonna take the battle
right to 'em.</i>

674
00:39:21,860 --> 00:39:23,903
[weapons blasting]

675
00:39:23,904 --> 00:39:28,282
Take your intergalactic asses
back home.

676
00:39:28,283 --> 00:39:29,659
Back home!

677
00:39:33,955 --> 00:39:36,707
[reporter 2] <i>As the global joint
military operation continues,</i>

678
00:39:36,708 --> 00:39:40,504
<i>this reporter can't help
but wonder, why are they here?</i>

679
00:39:42,714 --> 00:39:46,300
- The hell do they want?
- [reporter 2] <i>It is unclear
how long it'll take</i>

680
00:39:46,301 --> 00:39:49,136
<i>the world's forces to stop
the rampage of the invaders</i>

681
00:39:49,137 --> 00:39:51,555
<i>against critical
human resources.</i>

682
00:39:51,556 --> 00:39:54,934
<i>D.C. has publicly stated
that they will not speculate</i>

683
00:39:54,935 --> 00:39:57,728
<i>why they attacked
and what they could want.</i>

684
00:39:57,729 --> 00:40:00,189
<i>The attack is a total mystery.</i>

685
00:40:00,190 --> 00:40:02,358
<i>- All we know at this time...</i>
- Whoa.

686
00:40:02,359 --> 00:40:04,151
<i>...is that these machines
are making their way</i>

687
00:40:04,152 --> 00:40:06,445
<i>to what appears to be
predetermined destinations.</i>

688
00:40:06,446 --> 00:40:08,322
[heartbeat thumping rapidly]

689
00:40:08,323 --> 00:40:10,908
<i>They are clearly coordinated
and seem to have a plan.</i>

690
00:40:10,909 --> 00:40:14,620
<i>So far, nothing is able
to stop their advance,</i>

691
00:40:14,621 --> 00:40:16,622
<i>and the military
counteroffensive</i>

692
00:40:16,623 --> 00:40:20,334
<i>is continuing to bombard
their relentless procession.</i>

693
00:40:20,335 --> 00:40:22,420
[line ringing]

694
00:40:23,296 --> 00:40:25,297
<i>Dad, I got to get this thing
out of my leg.</i>

695
00:40:25,298 --> 00:40:27,424
No, no, no, no. Don't touch it.

696
00:40:27,425 --> 00:40:29,635
- [whimpers]
- Wait for Mark.

697
00:40:29,636 --> 00:40:31,345
[Faith breathing heavily]

698
00:40:31,346 --> 00:40:32,555
Hold on, honey.

699
00:40:32,556 --> 00:40:34,223
Just hold tight.

700
00:40:34,224 --> 00:40:36,142
I'll check on Mark.

701
00:40:36,143 --> 00:40:37,685
Do not touch that thing.

702
00:40:37,686 --> 00:40:39,228
Just relax.

703
00:40:39,229 --> 00:40:41,689
<i>- Oh, it hurts so bad.</i>
- [line ringing]

704
00:40:41,690 --> 00:40:42,815
Don't hang up, Faith.

705
00:40:42,816 --> 00:40:44,400
Mark, hurry up!

706
00:40:44,401 --> 00:40:46,861
<i>- I'm almost there, Pops.</i>
- You better be.

707
00:40:46,862 --> 00:40:48,821
You call me
soon as you get there, okay?

708
00:40:48,822 --> 00:40:50,197
<i>I will, I will.</i>

709
00:40:50,198 --> 00:40:51,575
<i>Oh, I'm cramping up.</i>

710
00:40:52,159 --> 00:40:54,160
- Okay, he's almost there, honey.
- [computer chimes]

711
00:40:54,161 --> 00:40:55,828
You sit tight.

712
00:40:55,829 --> 00:40:57,329
I'll come back to you.

713
00:40:57,330 --> 00:40:58,747
Just holler if you need me.

714
00:40:58,748 --> 00:40:59,916
I'll be right here, sweetheart.

715
00:41:05,005 --> 00:41:06,463
<i>Look.</i>

716
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:08,340
[heavy thudding]

717
00:41:08,341 --> 00:41:09,800
<i>It just stopped.</i>

718
00:41:09,801 --> 00:41:11,802
<i>It's changing directions.</i>

719
00:41:11,803 --> 00:41:13,513
<i>It's hunting for something,
Will.</i>

720
00:41:14,764 --> 00:41:16,390
[clattering, rumbling]

721
00:41:16,391 --> 00:41:18,518
[loud electronic humming]

722
00:41:21,938 --> 00:41:23,480
What's that sound?

723
00:41:23,481 --> 00:41:24,524
What the hell is that?

724
00:41:28,278 --> 00:41:32,115
Every time they make that sound,
they change directions.

725
00:41:38,079 --> 00:41:39,956
They're not trying
to communicate.

726
00:41:41,791 --> 00:41:43,210
They're trying to locate.

727
00:41:44,878 --> 00:41:46,338
What are you looking for?

728
00:42:15,033 --> 00:42:16,284
What are they doing?

729
00:42:29,422 --> 00:42:31,967
Now, what the hell
is that thing?

730
00:42:33,134 --> 00:42:34,427
[ringtone playing]

731
00:42:37,764 --> 00:42:40,307
<i>All right,
just-just hear me out on this.</i>

732
00:42:40,308 --> 00:42:42,017
<i>- The government...</i>
- No, no, no, no.

733
00:42:42,018 --> 00:42:43,727
I don't want to hear nothing
you have to say

734
00:42:43,728 --> 00:42:45,562
that starts off
with "the government."

735
00:42:45,563 --> 00:42:47,982
<i>The government's been keeping
secrets from you, Dad.</i>

736
00:42:47,983 --> 00:42:49,733
<i>From all of us.</i>

737
00:42:49,734 --> 00:42:51,944
<i>They have a surveillance
network that-that's</i>

738
00:42:51,945 --> 00:42:54,029
<i>a thousand times stronger
than anything
you could imagine.</i>

739
00:42:54,030 --> 00:42:56,365
You don't think I know
about the government
surveillance network?

740
00:42:56,366 --> 00:42:58,784
I am the government
surveillance network.

741
00:42:58,785 --> 00:42:59,868
<i>You don't know about this one!</i>

742
00:42:59,869 --> 00:43:01,745
- But you do?
<i>- Yes.</i>

743
00:43:01,746 --> 00:43:03,956
<i>- It's called Goliath.</i>
- That's fake news.

744
00:43:03,957 --> 00:43:05,582
<i>Think about it.
What do you think all these</i>

745
00:43:05,583 --> 00:43:07,293
<i>private space launch firms
are doing?</i>

746
00:43:07,294 --> 00:43:08,544
<i>All these secret satellites
they're launching?</i>

747
00:43:08,545 --> 00:43:10,004
That's Goliath?

748
00:43:10,005 --> 00:43:11,422
Some secret satellites?

749
00:43:11,423 --> 00:43:13,549
<i>Yes, yes.
Wirelessly transmitted</i>

750
00:43:13,550 --> 00:43:15,259
<i>to some underground facility
on the East Coast.</i>

751
00:43:15,260 --> 00:43:16,760
Jesus, Dave.

752
00:43:16,761 --> 00:43:18,262
<i>Dad, Dad, listen!</i>

753
00:43:18,263 --> 00:43:19,763
<i>Goliath collects
everything on us,</i>

754
00:43:19,764 --> 00:43:21,433
<i>and it won't stop
until they have it all.</i>

755
00:43:24,269 --> 00:43:27,229
Son, I love you,
but you got to leave this

756
00:43:27,230 --> 00:43:29,190
- conspiracy shit at the door.
- [ringtone playing]

757
00:43:32,861 --> 00:43:33,862
I got to go.

758
00:43:37,157 --> 00:43:39,325
<i>- Will, check this out.</i>
- [tires squealing]

759
00:43:39,326 --> 00:43:40,617
[automated announcement]
<i>Stay indoors.</i>

760
00:43:40,618 --> 00:43:42,453
<i>Keep away from windows.</i>

761
00:43:42,454 --> 00:43:44,288
[Sandra] <i>It looks like
a missile took it down.</i>

762
00:43:44,289 --> 00:43:46,582
<i>But it's still alive.
I can hear it.</i>

763
00:43:46,583 --> 00:43:48,334
That's One Wilshire.

764
00:43:48,335 --> 00:43:50,085
[automated announcement]
<i>Stay indoors.</i>

765
00:43:50,086 --> 00:43:52,254
[William] You know,
everywhere they've been going,

766
00:43:52,255 --> 00:43:54,256
- there's a data center.
<i>- Data center?</i>

767
00:43:54,257 --> 00:43:56,300
Yeah. They found
all the government servers.

768
00:43:56,301 --> 00:43:58,218
Look, I need you to get closer.

769
00:43:58,219 --> 00:44:00,262
<i>Yeah, yeah, yeah. Hang on.</i>

770
00:44:00,263 --> 00:44:01,847
[automated announcement]
<i>Take shelter.</i>

771
00:44:01,848 --> 00:44:02,891
<i>Stay indoors.</i>

772
00:44:04,351 --> 00:44:05,560
There, there. What's that?

773
00:44:09,314 --> 00:44:11,106
[Sandra]
Hold on. What is this thing?

774
00:44:11,107 --> 00:44:13,818
<i>What... This thing
looks alive, too.</i>

775
00:44:15,028 --> 00:44:18,072
<i>It looks like it smashed
its way into the building.</i>

776
00:44:18,073 --> 00:44:22,159
<i>- I'm going in.</i>
- Okay. Be careful.

777
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:24,411
[reporter]
<i>Reports are coming in
that the machines' destinations</i>

778
00:44:24,412 --> 00:44:27,664
<i>appear to be top secret
government data centers.</i>

779
00:44:27,665 --> 00:44:29,333
[William] Damn.

780
00:44:29,334 --> 00:44:30,959
My feeds are down.

781
00:44:30,960 --> 00:44:32,961
Can you get me
eyes on that thing?

782
00:44:32,962 --> 00:44:34,713
[reporter]
<i>Tripods around the globe</i>

783
00:44:34,714 --> 00:44:36,548
<i>have encircled
these facilities,</i>

784
00:44:36,549 --> 00:44:39,468
<i>but no one understands
why or what</i>

785
00:44:39,469 --> 00:44:41,720
<i>could be attracting them
to these locations.</i>

786
00:44:41,721 --> 00:44:43,722
[William]
What the hell is that stuff?

787
00:44:43,723 --> 00:44:45,724
[Sandra] <i>Something's going on
with the servers.</i>

788
00:44:45,725 --> 00:44:47,185
What in the world?

789
00:44:48,311 --> 00:44:50,687
[Sandra] <i>Will, th-this thing
is branched out everywhere,</i>

790
00:44:50,688 --> 00:44:52,689
<i>and it's-it's covering
the servers.</i>

791
00:44:52,690 --> 00:44:54,650
[William] Oh, shit.
They're in hyper download.

792
00:44:54,651 --> 00:44:56,151
They're being emptied.

793
00:44:56,152 --> 00:44:57,153
[Sandra] <i>Emptied?</i>

794
00:45:00,156 --> 00:45:01,990
<i>These are amazing.</i>

795
00:45:01,991 --> 00:45:04,243
Sandra, get out of there.

796
00:45:04,244 --> 00:45:05,494
<i>Oh, my God!</i>

797
00:45:05,495 --> 00:45:06,954
[whimpers, grunts]

798
00:45:06,955 --> 00:45:09,289
<i>- They're all over me!</i>
- Sandra!

799
00:45:09,290 --> 00:45:12,042
<i>- They're in my clothes.</i>
- [static droning]

800
00:45:12,043 --> 00:45:13,544
Sandra.

801
00:45:13,545 --> 00:45:15,463
Oh, shit.

802
00:45:17,674 --> 00:45:19,717
[line ringing]

803
00:45:21,052 --> 00:45:22,886
Come on, pick up.

804
00:45:22,887 --> 00:45:24,222
Pick up.

805
00:45:24,931 --> 00:45:26,306
Shit.

806
00:45:26,307 --> 00:45:28,643
[rapid beeping]

807
00:45:42,657 --> 00:45:44,741
[pilot] <i>Target acquired.
Missile locked.</i>

808
00:45:44,742 --> 00:45:47,202
<i>Shit! Abort, abort, abort!</i>

809
00:45:47,203 --> 00:45:48,246
[William] Oh, no.

810
00:45:52,709 --> 00:45:55,544
[reporter 1] <i>The Pentagon
has issued a dire report.</i>

811
00:45:55,545 --> 00:45:57,296
<i>The global military forces</i>

812
00:45:57,297 --> 00:45:59,840
<i>are experiencing
a complete cyberattack.</i>

813
00:45:59,841 --> 00:46:02,676
<i>Strategic Command
is not able to communicate</i>

814
00:46:02,677 --> 00:46:06,430
<i>with any forces,
and the world's
counteroffensive is crumbling</i>

815
00:46:06,431 --> 00:46:08,557
<i>as we report this to you now.</i>

816
00:46:08,558 --> 00:46:12,186
[soldier] <i>All systems have been
penetrated and data-drained.</i>

817
00:46:12,187 --> 00:46:16,064
<i>We must result to a full
manual attack at this point.</i>

818
00:46:16,065 --> 00:46:17,983
<i>There are no other options.</i>

819
00:46:17,984 --> 00:46:20,194
[weapons blasting]

820
00:46:20,195 --> 00:46:22,738
[reporter 2]
<i>The world's military
has been completely crippled.</i>

821
00:46:22,739 --> 00:46:24,823
[static crackling]

822
00:46:24,824 --> 00:46:26,784
- [alarm blaring]
- [indistinct shouting]

823
00:46:35,335 --> 00:46:37,085
[reporter 2] <i>Every system
has been penetrated</i>

824
00:46:37,086 --> 00:46:38,129
<i>and drained of data.</i>

825
00:46:38,630 --> 00:46:41,048
<i>Casualties are mounting
at a furious pace,</i>

826
00:46:41,049 --> 00:46:43,634
<i>and entire battalions
are retreating everywhere.</i>

827
00:46:43,635 --> 00:46:45,470
[loud electronic humming]

828
00:46:47,388 --> 00:46:49,390
[people screaming]

829
00:46:56,940 --> 00:46:58,440
[reporter 2]
<i>The military are sitting ducks</i>

830
00:46:58,441 --> 00:47:00,025
<i>and being slaughtered without</i>

831
00:47:00,026 --> 00:47:01,860
<i>their advanced digital systems</i>

832
00:47:01,861 --> 00:47:03,487
<i>and now engaging these invaders</i>

833
00:47:03,488 --> 00:47:06,281
<i>in what amounts to be
hand-to-hand combat</i>

834
00:47:06,282 --> 00:47:08,867
<i>just to get our troops
out of immediate harm's way</i>

835
00:47:08,868 --> 00:47:10,619
<i>before being
completely annihilated.</i>

836
00:47:10,620 --> 00:47:12,330
[ringtone playing]

837
00:47:14,082 --> 00:47:15,500
[second ringtone playing]

838
00:47:18,211 --> 00:47:19,628
<i>...reach you.
There's a problem.</i>

839
00:47:19,629 --> 00:47:21,004
Oh, so you made it?
What's going on?

840
00:47:21,005 --> 00:47:22,507
<i>Yeah, I'm-I'm with her,
but she's...</i>

841
00:47:24,384 --> 00:47:25,842
[pained, shaky breathing]

842
00:47:25,843 --> 00:47:27,886
- Sweetie.
- [Faith] <i>I thought that I could</i>

843
00:47:27,887 --> 00:47:30,264
<i>stop the bleeding
if I took it out.</i>

844
00:47:30,265 --> 00:47:32,266
- [whimpering]
- Mark. Mark!

845
00:47:32,267 --> 00:47:34,184
You need to do something.

846
00:47:34,185 --> 00:47:35,727
- [Mark] <i>Do what?</i> [stammering]
- [William] Something!

847
00:47:35,728 --> 00:47:37,021
- [Mark] <i>What can I do?</i>
- [ringtone playing]

848
00:47:39,440 --> 00:47:42,150
To stop the bleeding,
you got to put some pressure

849
00:47:42,151 --> 00:47:44,403
- on that wound, man.
- [Faith] <i>Okay, okay.</i>

850
00:47:44,404 --> 00:47:46,488
<i>- Okay.</i>
- No.

851
00:47:46,489 --> 00:47:47,948
Mark, no.

852
00:47:47,949 --> 00:47:49,366
You got to get
something else, man.

853
00:47:49,367 --> 00:47:50,785
- You need a tourniquet.
<i>- Trust me.</i>

854
00:47:53,079 --> 00:47:54,454
<i>I'm a pro.</i>

855
00:47:54,455 --> 00:47:56,331
That's not gonna work.

856
00:47:56,332 --> 00:47:58,417
<i>Dad, Dad, just...</i>

857
00:47:58,418 --> 00:47:59,793
[inhales deeply]

858
00:47:59,794 --> 00:48:01,795
<i>...have some faith.</i>

859
00:48:01,796 --> 00:48:03,673
[Faith groaning, whimpering]

860
00:48:07,051 --> 00:48:08,970
[heartbeat thumping rapidly]

861
00:48:09,929 --> 00:48:11,556
[Mark] <i>All right, it worked.</i>

862
00:48:12,307 --> 00:48:13,308
<i>Bleeding stopped.</i>

863
00:48:14,434 --> 00:48:15,685
<i>- Are you okay?</i>
- Mark.

864
00:48:16,811 --> 00:48:18,228
Keep me posted.

865
00:48:18,229 --> 00:48:19,688
<i>You got it, Pops.</i>

866
00:48:19,689 --> 00:48:21,481
[reporter] <i>Evacuations are now</i>

867
00:48:21,482 --> 00:48:23,692
<i>all that the world can do
to protect itself.</i>

868
00:48:23,693 --> 00:48:25,319
Okay, so you made it.
Good, good.

869
00:48:25,320 --> 00:48:26,945
- What's going on?
<i>- My new pets.</i>

870
00:48:26,946 --> 00:48:28,448
<i>Look. They even do tricks.</i>

871
00:48:32,535 --> 00:48:33,910
Hmm.

872
00:48:33,911 --> 00:48:35,912
Why are they going
after the chip?

873
00:48:35,913 --> 00:48:37,831
<i>The same reason
they love my phone.</i>

874
00:48:37,832 --> 00:48:39,833
<i>These little guys
are drawn to data.</i>

875
00:48:39,834 --> 00:48:42,002
- What do you mean
"drawn to data"?
<i>- It's intelligent.</i>

876
00:48:42,003 --> 00:48:43,545
<i>The more data it consumes,</i>

877
00:48:43,546 --> 00:48:45,631
<i>the smarter it gets.</i>

878
00:48:45,632 --> 00:48:47,758
These things eat data?

879
00:48:47,759 --> 00:48:49,468
<i>Exactly.</i>

880
00:48:49,469 --> 00:48:51,346
<i>That's why those servers
were being emptied.</i>

881
00:48:52,388 --> 00:48:53,806
Wait a minute.

882
00:48:56,309 --> 00:48:58,143
Holy shit.

883
00:48:58,144 --> 00:49:00,103
This whole attack
is just a big diversion

884
00:49:00,104 --> 00:49:02,564
to get those Tripods
to the data centers.

885
00:49:02,565 --> 00:49:05,150
And those Tripods
are just Trojan horses

886
00:49:05,151 --> 00:49:07,527
to get those little bugs
into the servers.

887
00:49:07,528 --> 00:49:09,405
[William and Sandra]
To get to the data.

888
00:49:19,374 --> 00:49:21,000
Hey, I'll circle back.

889
00:49:22,168 --> 00:49:24,211
[reporter] <i>Tanker ships
around the globe are frozen</i>

890
00:49:24,212 --> 00:49:27,631
<i>without any GPS data,
and oil rigs are combusting.</i>

891
00:49:27,632 --> 00:49:29,883
This is terrible.

892
00:49:29,884 --> 00:49:34,137
[reporter] <i>Commercial airlines
are grounded by the FAA,</i>

893
00:49:34,138 --> 00:49:37,015
<i>but those still in the air
have no way to navigate</i>

894
00:49:37,016 --> 00:49:39,811
<i>as their onboard systems
have failed.</i>

895
00:49:41,145 --> 00:49:43,480
<i>Nuclear power facilities
are paralyzed</i>

896
00:49:43,481 --> 00:49:46,191
<i>and are not able
to generate electricity.</i>

897
00:49:46,192 --> 00:49:49,403
- [horns honking]
<i>- With traffic
escaping cities in gridlock,</i>

898
00:49:49,404 --> 00:49:52,656
<i>there's no way to get away
from the invasion.</i>

899
00:49:52,657 --> 00:49:55,534
<i>Power grids are collapsing
in mass numbers.</i>

900
00:49:55,535 --> 00:49:58,370
<i>The world is going dark
as we speak.</i>

901
00:49:58,371 --> 00:50:01,331
<i>Financial data has been
completely drained and erased,</i>

902
00:50:01,332 --> 00:50:03,166
<i>making the Earth's population</i>

903
00:50:03,167 --> 00:50:04,918
<i>- totally bankrupt.</i>
- My God.

904
00:50:04,919 --> 00:50:07,045
<i>Reports from around the world
show mass rioting</i>

905
00:50:07,046 --> 00:50:09,297
<i>and looting
to get whatever they can.</i>

906
00:50:09,298 --> 00:50:11,925
<i>We are in utter chaos</i>

907
00:50:11,926 --> 00:50:14,511
<i>without our most precious
resource: our data.</i>

908
00:50:14,512 --> 00:50:16,806
[William] Shit!

909
00:50:24,313 --> 00:50:26,399
No. No, no, no. No, no!

910
00:50:30,319 --> 00:50:31,945
[Erika, recorded] <i>Remember
to take out the trash today</i>

911
00:50:31,946 --> 00:50:33,739
<i>and be nice to the kids.</i>

912
00:50:33,740 --> 00:50:35,657
<i>I love you, baby.</i>

913
00:50:35,658 --> 00:50:37,409
[audio distorting] <i>Remember
to take out the trash today</i>

914
00:50:37,410 --> 00:50:39,954
<i>and be nice to the kids.</i>

915
00:50:49,756 --> 00:50:50,757
Fuck!

916
00:51:08,149 --> 00:51:09,859
[distorted voice speaking]

917
00:51:37,762 --> 00:51:38,763
<i>It's too late now.</i>

918
00:52:00,576 --> 00:52:01,661
[sighs heavily]

919
00:52:06,833 --> 00:52:08,583
[distorted voice] <i>It won't stop
until they have it all.</i>

920
00:52:08,584 --> 00:52:10,627
<i>It won't stop
until they have it all.</i>

921
00:52:10,628 --> 00:52:12,629
<i>- It won't stop
until they have it all.</i>
- Whoa.

922
00:52:12,630 --> 00:52:14,548
<i>It won't stop
until they have it all.</i>

923
00:52:14,549 --> 00:52:17,176
[pitch lowering] <i>It won't stop
until they have it all.</i>

924
00:52:19,804 --> 00:52:22,889
[pitch increasing] <i>It won't stop
until they have it all.</i>

925
00:52:22,890 --> 00:52:25,851
[voice normalizing]
<i>It won't stop
until they have it all.</i>

926
00:52:25,852 --> 00:52:31,898
<i>It won't stop
until they have it all.</i>

927
00:52:31,899 --> 00:52:34,234
[David] <i>It won't stop
until they have it all.</i>

928
00:52:34,235 --> 00:52:36,863
[David's voice echoing]

929
00:52:42,702 --> 00:52:44,036
It's you?!

930
00:52:45,454 --> 00:52:47,539
- It's you.
- [David] <i>Yeah.</i>

931
00:52:47,540 --> 00:52:49,416
<i>Well, yes, kind of. I...</i>

932
00:52:49,417 --> 00:52:51,126
- How could you, man?
<i>- Yeah.</i>

933
00:52:51,127 --> 00:52:52,752
How could you?

934
00:52:52,753 --> 00:52:55,672
My own son is hacking
the government.

935
00:52:55,673 --> 00:52:58,843
<i>You know, for someone
who spends their life watching,
you sure do miss a lot.</i>

936
00:52:59,969 --> 00:53:01,428
<i>Look, the past is the past.</i>

937
00:53:01,429 --> 00:53:04,015
<i>I'm ready to work together now.
Are you?</i>

938
00:53:09,395 --> 00:53:10,605
I got to go.

939
00:53:11,814 --> 00:53:13,857
[reporter]
<i>All you see is broken glass.</i>

940
00:53:13,858 --> 00:53:16,651
<i>Businesses are all closed,
and the people need supplies.</i>

941
00:53:16,652 --> 00:53:18,905
<i>-It's dog-eat-dog out here.</i>
- [computer chimes]

942
00:53:50,686 --> 00:53:52,730
[dramatic music]

943
00:54:00,154 --> 00:54:01,656
[William] Oh, my God.

944
00:54:09,956 --> 00:54:11,123
What is this?

945
00:54:14,043 --> 00:54:17,004
"Violent weather,"
"strange craft sightings."

946
00:54:18,756 --> 00:54:20,216
What the hell are those things?

947
00:54:24,261 --> 00:54:27,931
Collecting data? Ah, man.

948
00:54:27,932 --> 00:54:30,016
That's what brought them here
in the first place.

949
00:54:30,017 --> 00:54:31,476
They knew.

950
00:54:31,477 --> 00:54:34,354
They knew,
and they hid it from us.

951
00:54:34,355 --> 00:54:35,856
They hid it from everybody.

952
00:54:43,072 --> 00:54:44,907
They even knew
about these things.

953
00:54:52,999 --> 00:54:55,834
Goliath. Damn.

954
00:54:55,835 --> 00:54:57,752
Dave was right.

955
00:54:57,753 --> 00:54:59,963
They lied to me the whole time.

956
00:54:59,964 --> 00:55:01,257
Right to my face.

957
00:55:04,635 --> 00:55:06,594
Holy shit.

958
00:55:06,595 --> 00:55:08,722
Briggs is behind
the whole thing.

959
00:55:08,723 --> 00:55:11,058
No wonder he wanted
to catch the Disruptor.

960
00:55:15,563 --> 00:55:18,314
[General, recorded]
<i>It's too risky, Briggs.
Shut it down now.</i>

961
00:55:18,315 --> 00:55:20,275
[Briggs, recorded]
<i>With all due respect, General,</i>

962
00:55:20,276 --> 00:55:22,444
<i>Goliath will be activated
whether you like it or not.</i>

963
00:55:22,445 --> 00:55:24,571
<i>It's the greatest
surveillance system</i>

964
00:55:24,572 --> 00:55:26,573
<i>- the world has ever seen.</i>
- [General]
<i>They will come for it.</i>

965
00:55:26,574 --> 00:55:28,116
<i>It'll be a full invasion,
damn it.</i>

966
00:55:28,117 --> 00:55:29,909
[Briggs] <i>Invasion?
We now have the ability</i>

967
00:55:29,910 --> 00:55:31,411
<i>to predict every person's
thoughts and movements.</i>

968
00:55:31,412 --> 00:55:32,787
<i>It's total control.</i>

969
00:55:32,788 --> 00:55:34,247
[William] So Briggs went rogue,

970
00:55:34,248 --> 00:55:36,416
put the whole damn thing
in this building

971
00:55:36,417 --> 00:55:37,751
right under my feet?

972
00:55:37,752 --> 00:55:39,294
[General] <i>You crazy bastard.</i>

973
00:55:39,295 --> 00:55:41,463
<i>You can't act alone on this,
Briggs.</i>

974
00:55:41,464 --> 00:55:43,173
[Briggs]
<i>Oh, really? Watch me, General.</i>

975
00:55:43,174 --> 00:55:45,217
[ringtone playing]

976
00:55:46,427 --> 00:55:48,011
Yeah, I know all about Goliath.

977
00:55:48,012 --> 00:55:50,555
<i>Wow. You did it.</i>

978
00:55:50,556 --> 00:55:52,307
<i>I can always spot talent.</i>

979
00:55:52,308 --> 00:55:54,893
NASA warned you,
if you activated Goliath,

980
00:55:54,894 --> 00:55:57,062
it could spark an invasion.

981
00:55:57,063 --> 00:56:00,273
<i>Those dinosaur bureaucrats
don't keep us safe. I do!</i>

982
00:56:00,274 --> 00:56:02,400
When you turned on Goliath,
you rang a dinner bell

983
00:56:02,401 --> 00:56:04,527
that traveled throughout
the whole galaxy.

984
00:56:04,528 --> 00:56:06,905
<i>Don't worry,
they won't get into Goliath.</i>

985
00:56:06,906 --> 00:56:09,032
<i>I air-gapped the entire system.</i>

986
00:56:09,033 --> 00:56:11,367
<i>We're safe. I kept us safe.</i>

987
00:56:11,368 --> 00:56:15,288
You risked all of our lives
just to spy on people's
Amazon carts!

988
00:56:15,289 --> 00:56:16,956
<i>Come on, Radford.</i>

989
00:56:16,957 --> 00:56:19,167
<i>The government's
like mommy and daddy.</i>

990
00:56:19,168 --> 00:56:21,711
<i>If we can't track our babies,
how can we protect them?</i>

991
00:56:21,712 --> 00:56:23,296
Is that what this is about?

992
00:56:23,297 --> 00:56:25,298
Well, my family's not protected.

993
00:56:25,299 --> 00:56:27,342
They're not safe.

994
00:56:27,343 --> 00:56:30,678
<i>DHS building is
a goddamn bunker.</i>

995
00:56:30,679 --> 00:56:32,263
<i>Goliath is 40 feet underground.</i>

996
00:56:32,264 --> 00:56:34,057
<i>There's no way
they can get to it.</i>

997
00:56:34,058 --> 00:56:36,267
<i>- I made sure of it.</i>
- You're insane.

998
00:56:36,268 --> 00:56:39,270
I didn't sign up for this shit.
No way, ho how.

999
00:56:39,271 --> 00:56:41,689
<i>Well, then, thank you
for your service, Radford.</i>

1000
00:56:41,690 --> 00:56:43,775
<i>- You're dismissed.</i>
- Got to stop this thing. Wait!

1001
00:56:43,776 --> 00:56:45,693
[crowd clamoring on video]

1002
00:56:45,694 --> 00:56:46,946
[static crackling]

1003
00:56:48,322 --> 00:56:50,157
Come on. No, no, no, no.

1004
00:56:55,287 --> 00:56:56,580
Shit.

1005
00:56:59,959 --> 00:57:01,252
Damn it.

1006
00:57:03,379 --> 00:57:05,047
Oh, no.

1007
00:57:18,352 --> 00:57:20,604
[tense music]

1008
00:57:32,074 --> 00:57:33,993
[distorted voice speaking]

1009
00:57:44,211 --> 00:57:46,380
You clever little shit.

1010
00:57:48,090 --> 00:57:49,258
Love you, boy.

1011
00:58:00,978 --> 00:58:02,687
Touchdown.

1012
00:58:02,688 --> 00:58:05,648
Touchdown! Touchdown!

1013
00:58:05,649 --> 00:58:07,401
Kiss my ass, Briggs.

1014
00:58:16,118 --> 00:58:17,828
How you like me now?

1015
00:58:21,207 --> 00:58:22,374
William Radford.

1016
00:58:43,562 --> 00:58:44,563
Good.

1017
00:58:45,773 --> 00:58:46,982
Thank God.

1018
00:58:51,237 --> 00:58:53,780
Okay. So what do we do?

1019
00:58:53,781 --> 00:58:56,658
<i>All right.
What if we starve them out?</i>

1020
00:58:56,659 --> 00:58:59,035
<i>Take away the data, flood
the servers until they crash.</i>

1021
00:58:59,036 --> 00:59:01,079
You mean
a denial-of-service attack?

1022
00:59:01,080 --> 00:59:02,830
<i>- Exactly.</i>
- Nah.

1023
00:59:02,831 --> 00:59:04,333
A D-DoS won't cut it.

1024
00:59:05,459 --> 00:59:08,253
We got to poison
they food supply, okay?

1025
00:59:08,254 --> 00:59:11,464
So we got to infect
all the data centers.

1026
00:59:11,465 --> 00:59:13,758
Come with a good old-fashioned
rabbit virus.

1027
00:59:13,759 --> 00:59:16,302
<i>Yo, that's what
I'm talking about.
Dad, that-that's classic.</i>

1028
00:59:16,303 --> 00:59:20,181
We got to go old-school.
The bigger they are,
the harder they fall.

1029
00:59:20,182 --> 00:59:22,433
<i>- Exactly.</i>
- Now, one thing I know:

1030
00:59:22,434 --> 00:59:26,229
No way, no how can you and I
write this virus alone.

1031
00:59:26,230 --> 00:59:29,565
<i>Well, not alone,
but if we had the right team.</i>

1032
00:59:29,566 --> 00:59:31,317
Okay. I'll make some calls.

1033
00:59:31,318 --> 00:59:32,695
[chuckles softly]

1034
00:59:33,779 --> 00:59:35,196
What's so funny?

1035
00:59:35,197 --> 00:59:37,991
<i>Nothing.
Just, everyone you know sucks.</i>

1036
00:59:37,992 --> 00:59:39,617
<i>I'll make the calls.</i>

1037
00:59:39,618 --> 00:59:41,370
All right, Disruptor.

1038
00:59:43,163 --> 00:59:44,623
Let's disrupt some shit.

1039
00:59:47,960 --> 00:59:50,170
[David]
<i>Dad, meet my Disruptors.</i>

1040
00:59:50,879 --> 00:59:52,588
[Code Crusher, distorted]
<i>Your dad's DHS.</i>

1041
00:59:52,589 --> 00:59:54,340
[Thelma & Louise]
<i>He's the goddamn enemy.</i>

1042
00:59:54,341 --> 00:59:56,009
[Starfire] <i>What the hell?
You turn on us, Dave?</i>

1043
00:59:56,010 --> 00:59:57,427
- Lord have mercy.
- [Burnout] <i>I thought this was</i>

1044
00:59:57,428 --> 00:59:58,928
<i>supposed to be our safe space.</i>

1045
00:59:58,929 --> 01:00:00,638
[David] <i>Guys, guys, enough.</i>

1046
01:00:00,639 --> 01:00:03,891
<i>These aliens are here
for one reason: Goliath.</i>

1047
01:00:03,892 --> 01:00:07,061
<i>We thought shit was bad now,
once they get access to it,
it's over.</i>

1048
01:00:07,062 --> 01:00:08,980
[Starfire]
<i>So, what do you want to do?</i>

1049
01:00:08,981 --> 01:00:10,857
<i>We use the data centers
they've connected to as bait</i>

1050
01:00:10,858 --> 01:00:12,734
<i>and plant an old-school
rabbit virus</i>

1051
01:00:12,735 --> 01:00:14,444
<i>to infect the data
they're eating.</i>

1052
01:00:14,445 --> 01:00:16,821
<i>My dad's DHS connections
will get us in.</i>

1053
01:00:16,822 --> 01:00:19,282
<i>But we must get
the rabbit virus payload
uploaded.</i>

1054
01:00:19,283 --> 01:00:21,660
[Burnout] <i>Your dad's
got to give us total immunity.</i>

1055
01:00:22,661 --> 01:00:24,955
[William] All right, fellas.
That's a deal.

1056
01:00:28,208 --> 01:00:32,962
And... your records are wiped.

1057
01:00:32,963 --> 01:00:34,630
<i>I'll create the rabbit virus.</i>

1058
01:00:34,631 --> 01:00:36,924
<i>Starfire,
brute-force passwords.</i>

1059
01:00:36,925 --> 01:00:39,093
<i>Thelma & Louise,
break encryption.</i>

1060
01:00:39,094 --> 01:00:41,054
<i>Code Crusher, bypass firewalls.</i>

1061
01:00:41,055 --> 01:00:43,973
<i>And, Burnout,
just stay out of trouble.</i>

1062
01:00:43,974 --> 01:00:45,558
[Burnout]
<i>I'll steal the SSL keys</i>

1063
01:00:45,559 --> 01:00:46,976
<i>and start hijacking
user credentials.</i>

1064
01:00:46,977 --> 01:00:48,312
[Code Crusher]
<i>All right, let's go.</i>

1065
01:00:57,696 --> 01:01:00,323
Just whipping up
a little something-something.

1066
01:01:00,324 --> 01:01:01,533
<i>Okay.</i>

1067
01:01:04,453 --> 01:01:07,039
[typing]

1068
01:01:16,423 --> 01:01:18,299
[William] This is the last time

1069
01:01:18,300 --> 01:01:21,303
you ever spy on someone again,
Briggs.

1070
01:01:22,221 --> 01:01:24,264
[distorted voice speaking]

1071
01:01:30,187 --> 01:01:32,814
[General, recorded]
<i>It's too risky, Briggs.
Shut it down now.</i>

1072
01:01:32,815 --> 01:01:34,357
[Briggs, recorded]
<i>With all due respect, General,</i>

1073
01:01:34,358 --> 01:01:35,691
<i>Goliath will be activated</i>

1074
01:01:35,692 --> 01:01:37,276
<i>whether you like it or not.</i>

1075
01:01:37,277 --> 01:01:39,404
<i>It's the greatest
surveillance system</i>

1076
01:01:39,405 --> 01:01:41,114
<i>-the world has ever seen.</i>
- [General]
<i>They will come for it.</i>

1077
01:01:41,115 --> 01:01:42,573
<i>It'll be a full invasion,
damn it.</i>

1078
01:01:42,574 --> 01:01:44,659
[Briggs]
<i>Invasion? Give me a break.</i>

1079
01:01:44,660 --> 01:01:46,869
<i>We now have the ability
to predict every person's</i>

1080
01:01:46,870 --> 01:01:48,913
<i>thoughts and movements.</i>

1081
01:01:48,914 --> 01:01:51,332
[distorted voice] <i>Our most
precious resource on Earth</i>

1082
01:01:51,333 --> 01:01:54,627
<i>is food
for the superior intelligence
that invaded Earth.</i>

1083
01:01:54,628 --> 01:01:56,462
<i>The government knew
this would happen,</i>

1084
01:01:56,463 --> 01:01:58,048
<i>and they activated Goliath
anyway.</i>

1085
01:01:59,258 --> 01:02:01,259
[David] <i>Holy shit, Dad.</i>

1086
01:02:01,260 --> 01:02:03,136
[Code Crusher] <i>Your dad's OG.</i>

1087
01:02:03,137 --> 01:02:06,097
[Burnout] <i>Damn, Mr. Radford,
that was badass.</i>

1088
01:02:06,098 --> 01:02:08,182
[William] How you like me now?

1089
01:02:08,183 --> 01:02:10,686
- [helicopter blades whirring]
- [distant siren wailing]

1090
01:02:11,770 --> 01:02:13,646
Man, I can't believe
I just did that.

1091
01:02:13,647 --> 01:02:15,064
<i>Congratulations, Dad.</i>

1092
01:02:15,065 --> 01:02:16,858
<i>You're officially a Disruptor.</i>

1093
01:02:16,859 --> 01:02:18,110
<i>Welcome to the crew.</i>

1094
01:02:19,319 --> 01:02:20,987
<i>All right,
we got the rabbit virus.</i>

1095
01:02:20,988 --> 01:02:22,448
<i>Sending it to you now.</i>

1096
01:02:30,080 --> 01:02:32,166
Bombs away.

1097
01:02:39,298 --> 01:02:40,966
All right,
the virus is launched.

1098
01:02:42,593 --> 01:02:45,052
[David] <i>Here we go, here we go.</i>

1099
01:02:45,053 --> 01:02:47,514
[Burnout]
<i>Been waiting to take down
the government for years.</i>

1100
01:02:48,932 --> 01:02:51,726
[loud electronic humming]

1101
01:02:51,727 --> 01:02:53,270
Eat it up.

1102
01:02:54,354 --> 01:02:55,646
- [loud electronic humming]
- Eat it up.

1103
01:02:55,647 --> 01:02:56,982
Yeah, eat it.

1104
01:02:59,234 --> 01:03:00,485
Damn it.

1105
01:03:00,486 --> 01:03:02,279
Something's wrong.

1106
01:03:04,781 --> 01:03:06,741
[Code Crusher] <i>I'm being hacked.
They're hacking us!</i>

1107
01:03:06,742 --> 01:03:08,409
[Starfire]
<i>They're eating our data.</i>

1108
01:03:08,410 --> 01:03:10,286
<i>My data's being drained!</i>

1109
01:03:10,287 --> 01:03:12,038
[Code Crusher] <i>They're gonna
find Goliath with it.</i>

1110
01:03:12,039 --> 01:03:13,415
[William] Are you serious?

1111
01:03:14,500 --> 01:03:15,667
Look at this.

1112
01:03:23,800 --> 01:03:25,635
[soldier] <i>You're freaking
breaking up, man.</i>

1113
01:03:25,636 --> 01:03:26,720
<i>Oh, my God!</i>

1114
01:03:31,767 --> 01:03:33,267
[loud electronic humming]

1115
01:03:33,268 --> 01:03:34,895
<i>Shit, shit, shit.</i>

1116
01:03:36,188 --> 01:03:37,939
<i>Shit!</i>

1117
01:03:37,940 --> 01:03:40,191
[reporter] <i>The Capitol
is under full attack!</i>

1118
01:03:40,192 --> 01:03:42,569
[people screaming]

1119
01:03:44,446 --> 01:03:46,322
[William]
You guys are totally exposed.

1120
01:03:46,323 --> 01:03:47,699
They got your IPs.

1121
01:03:49,159 --> 01:03:51,285
Y'all got to get out of there.

1122
01:03:51,286 --> 01:03:52,620
- Haul ass now!
<i>- Oh, my God.</i>

1123
01:03:52,621 --> 01:03:53,913
<i>Oh, my God! Oh, my God!</i>

1124
01:03:53,914 --> 01:03:54,915
Shit.

1125
01:04:02,881 --> 01:04:04,757
Hey! Get out of there!

1126
01:04:04,758 --> 01:04:05,801
[loud electronic humming]

1127
01:04:09,221 --> 01:04:10,388
<i>Starfire!</i>

1128
01:04:10,389 --> 01:04:11,807
[loud electronic humming]

1129
01:04:15,394 --> 01:04:17,144
[William] Hey.

1130
01:04:17,145 --> 01:04:18,772
It's near our house.

1131
01:04:20,107 --> 01:04:21,649
No, no, that...

1132
01:04:21,650 --> 01:04:23,651
Dave, get out of there now!

1133
01:04:23,652 --> 01:04:25,611
Dave, it's out... No!

1134
01:04:25,612 --> 01:04:27,613
- [loud electronic humming]
- Dave!

1135
01:04:27,614 --> 01:04:28,824
No!

1136
01:04:30,450 --> 01:04:31,577
No!

1137
01:04:38,208 --> 01:04:40,876
He's okay. He's okay. He's okay.

1138
01:04:40,877 --> 01:04:42,921
[line ringing]

1139
01:04:44,923 --> 01:04:46,800
- [breathing heavily]
- [typing]

1140
01:04:52,389 --> 01:04:53,724
No.

1141
01:04:54,975 --> 01:04:57,311
[muttering under breath]
He's okay, he's okay. He's okay.

1142
01:04:59,938 --> 01:05:01,939
[reporter]
<i>Reports are flooding in
of massive destruction</i>

1143
01:05:01,940 --> 01:05:05,151
<i>that has just occurred
at several global locations.</i>

1144
01:05:05,152 --> 01:05:07,194
<i>We're hearing that
these machines have separated</i>

1145
01:05:07,195 --> 01:05:09,405
<i>from their legs and are
attacking specific targets.</i>

1146
01:05:09,406 --> 01:05:11,574
[William whispering]
He's okay. He's okay.

1147
01:05:11,575 --> 01:05:13,284
[reporter] <i>We don't know
how many casualties
have been incurred,</i>

1148
01:05:13,285 --> 01:05:15,536
<i>but the destruction
is said to be absolute</i>

1149
01:05:15,537 --> 01:05:18,080
<i>and that no one
could have survived.</i>

1150
01:05:18,081 --> 01:05:20,166
<i>Emergency services
are overwhelmed and are unable</i>

1151
01:05:20,167 --> 01:05:22,960
<i>to provide any rescue personnel
at this time.</i>

1152
01:05:22,961 --> 01:05:25,005
[line continues ringing]

1153
01:05:33,680 --> 01:05:34,973
Okay, okay.

1154
01:05:45,025 --> 01:05:46,652
[line stops ringing]

1155
01:05:59,790 --> 01:06:00,874
[ringtone playing]

1156
01:06:07,547 --> 01:06:08,964
Dave?

1157
01:06:08,965 --> 01:06:10,717
Son, is-is that you?

1158
01:06:16,765 --> 01:06:18,850
[ringtone playing]

1159
01:06:21,603 --> 01:06:22,646
Dave?

1160
01:06:25,148 --> 01:06:27,567
What is this?

1161
01:06:29,236 --> 01:06:31,654
<i>That was freaking intense.</i>

1162
01:06:31,655 --> 01:06:33,406
My God, man!

1163
01:06:33,407 --> 01:06:34,699
I...

1164
01:06:34,700 --> 01:06:36,826
I thought you got hurt.
I-I thought...

1165
01:06:36,827 --> 01:06:38,619
I thought you was in the house.

1166
01:06:38,620 --> 01:06:40,788
<i>- Oh, you thought I was home.</i>
- This is crazy.

1167
01:06:40,789 --> 01:06:42,874
<i>Nah, I bounced my signal.
I'm chilling at Brian's house.</i>

1168
01:06:46,962 --> 01:06:49,088
You had me
worried to death, man.

1169
01:06:49,089 --> 01:06:51,757
<i>Why do you think you couldn't
find Disruptor for a year?</i>

1170
01:06:51,758 --> 01:06:54,135
Yeah, but...

1171
01:06:54,136 --> 01:06:55,720
- but they blew up my house.
<i>- Uh-huh.</i>

1172
01:06:55,721 --> 01:06:57,138
They blew up my house, man.

1173
01:06:57,139 --> 01:06:59,098
- I...
<i>- Dad, Dad, let's focus.</i>

1174
01:06:59,099 --> 01:07:01,350
Why couldn't you run that signal
through Brian's house

1175
01:07:01,351 --> 01:07:03,436
- so they can blow
his shit up, huh?
<i>- Look, Dad.</i>

1176
01:07:03,437 --> 01:07:05,146
<i>We got a lot
of work to do, so...</i>

1177
01:07:05,147 --> 01:07:06,897
I don't have
alien invasion insurance.

1178
01:07:06,898 --> 01:07:08,358
[ringtone playing]

1179
01:07:09,860 --> 01:07:11,403
I'll circle back.

1180
01:07:14,990 --> 01:07:17,325
<i>Hey, I have to
show you something.</i>

1181
01:07:18,326 --> 01:07:20,119
[sighs]

1182
01:07:20,120 --> 01:07:23,080
It looks like plastic,
metal, and silicon.

1183
01:07:23,081 --> 01:07:26,000
<i>Right, like everything you'd
expect to see on a microchip.</i>

1184
01:07:26,001 --> 01:07:28,336
<i>But look here.</i>

1185
01:07:29,921 --> 01:07:31,672
Shit.

1186
01:07:31,673 --> 01:07:34,008
Why is there blood
inside of a computer chip?

1187
01:07:34,009 --> 01:07:38,220
<i>They're a hybrid organism:
biological and cyber.</i>

1188
01:07:38,221 --> 01:07:41,599
<i>- I mean, look,
there's even DNA.</i>
- DNA?

1189
01:07:41,600 --> 01:07:45,186
- Oh, my God.
- [Sandra] <i>Life and computers
becoming one.</i>

1190
01:07:45,187 --> 01:07:46,396
[William]
Hold tight. Hold tight.

1191
01:07:48,857 --> 01:07:51,358
Faith, do you have access
to your cannibal code?

1192
01:07:51,359 --> 01:07:52,694
[Faith] <i>You know about that?</i>

1193
01:07:53,820 --> 01:07:55,780
These things are alive.

1194
01:07:55,781 --> 01:07:58,991
- That means we can kill 'em.
<i>- It's never been tested.</i>

1195
01:07:58,992 --> 01:08:02,119
<i>They're a hybrid organism:
biological and cyber.</i>

1196
01:08:02,120 --> 01:08:03,996
<i>That explains why
a computer virus
couldn't stop 'em.</i>

1197
01:08:03,997 --> 01:08:06,248
- Exactly.
<i>- DNA's
a lot like computer code.</i>

1198
01:08:06,249 --> 01:08:08,501
<i>Why can't you just reprogram
the DNA in the aliens</i>

1199
01:08:08,502 --> 01:08:10,169
<i>to cannibalize themselves?</i>

1200
01:08:10,170 --> 01:08:12,087
<i>Mark, that's absolutely right.</i>

1201
01:08:12,088 --> 01:08:13,881
<i>- We-we can rewrite
Faith's code.</i>
- [William] Okay.

1202
01:08:13,882 --> 01:08:16,842
Here's what we do:
We upload it to Goliath.

1203
01:08:16,843 --> 01:08:19,220
<i>How would we get it
into Goliath?</i>

1204
01:08:19,221 --> 01:08:20,387
I'll worry about that.

1205
01:08:20,388 --> 01:08:21,972
Dave, Faith,

1206
01:08:21,973 --> 01:08:24,350
you guys just work on that code
and get it to me.

1207
01:08:24,351 --> 01:08:25,893
[Faith] <i>Okay, I'll send Dave
the DNA sequence</i>

1208
01:08:25,894 --> 01:08:27,646
<i>so he can translate it
into code.</i>

1209
01:08:39,407 --> 01:08:41,618
[William]
Hmm. We'll see about that.

1210
01:08:54,297 --> 01:08:57,174
[General]
<i>The Goliath server complex
is deep underground at DHS.</i>

1211
01:08:57,175 --> 01:09:00,344
<i>We must collapse
the DHS building on top of it.</i>

1212
01:09:00,345 --> 01:09:03,514
<i>A 40-foot pile of rubble on top
won't allow them to get to it.</i>

1213
01:09:03,515 --> 01:09:04,932
<i>We're out of time.</i>

1214
01:09:04,933 --> 01:09:07,810
<i>We must bomb D.C.
to stop their advance.</i>

1215
01:09:07,811 --> 01:09:09,770
<i>We must destroy DHS
to make sure</i>

1216
01:09:09,771 --> 01:09:11,897
<i>anything that gets through
can't get to Goliath.</i>

1217
01:09:11,898 --> 01:09:13,524
No!

1218
01:09:13,525 --> 01:09:15,484
[Crystal]
<i>Military has POTUS's authority</i>

1219
01:09:15,485 --> 01:09:18,737
<i>to combat this threat
with any means necessary.</i>

1220
01:09:18,738 --> 01:09:20,239
[General]
<i>Our estimated blast radius</i>

1221
01:09:20,240 --> 01:09:22,366
<i>for the D.C. area
is five miles.</i>

1222
01:09:22,367 --> 01:09:25,035
<i>We've already begun
immediate evacuations...</i>

1223
01:09:25,036 --> 01:09:26,787
- Hell no.
<i>- ...although casualties
will be very high.</i>

1224
01:09:26,788 --> 01:09:28,455
- [alarm blaring]
<i>- I've initiated lockdown of</i>

1225
01:09:28,456 --> 01:09:30,332
<i>our most sensitive
government buildings</i>

1226
01:09:30,333 --> 01:09:32,543
<i>in preparation
for the incoming bombing.</i>

1227
01:09:32,544 --> 01:09:34,879
<i>DHS is to be hit twice</i>

1228
01:09:34,880 --> 01:09:37,882
<i>and twice as hard
to ensure total destruction.</i>

1229
01:09:37,883 --> 01:09:39,925
We're out of time.

1230
01:09:39,926 --> 01:09:41,468
They're gonna bomb D.C. and DHS.

1231
01:09:41,469 --> 01:09:43,304
We got to get that
cannibal code in 'em fast.

1232
01:09:43,305 --> 01:09:44,930
<i>Dad, you're gonna
have to get the code</i>

1233
01:09:44,931 --> 01:09:46,724
<i>- into the servers manually.</i>
- Exactly.

1234
01:09:46,725 --> 01:09:48,809
<i>No, the code
you will be carrying is data.</i>

1235
01:09:48,810 --> 01:09:50,352
<i>They're gonna devour you
along with it.</i>

1236
01:09:50,353 --> 01:09:52,271
- I'll be fine.
<i>- Dad.</i>

1237
01:09:52,272 --> 01:09:53,647
<i>- They will kill you, Will.</i>
- I'll be fine.

1238
01:09:53,648 --> 01:09:54,732
<i>It's a damn suicide mission.</i>

1239
01:09:54,733 --> 01:09:56,443
I said I'll be fine.

1240
01:09:57,777 --> 01:09:59,070
We're out of options.

1241
01:10:34,230 --> 01:10:36,690
<i>All right, the code is ready.</i>

1242
01:10:36,691 --> 01:10:38,484
<i>Sending it to you now.</i>

1243
01:10:38,485 --> 01:10:39,944
<i>Put it on a thumb drive.</i>

1244
01:10:39,945 --> 01:10:41,654
I don't have a thumb drive.

1245
01:10:41,655 --> 01:10:44,114
<i>What do you mean
you don't have a thumb drive?</i>

1246
01:10:44,115 --> 01:10:46,075
<i>Even I have a thumb drive.</i>

1247
01:10:46,076 --> 01:10:48,661
Boy, this is a top secret
military installation.

1248
01:10:48,662 --> 01:10:51,414
They don't let thumb drives
in the building.

1249
01:10:52,499 --> 01:10:54,917
<i>Um, Faith can load it here
and I can get it to you.</i>

1250
01:10:54,918 --> 01:10:56,794
How?

1251
01:10:56,795 --> 01:10:57,796
<i>Prime Air.</i>

1252
01:10:59,130 --> 01:11:00,256
Prime Air?

1253
01:11:03,259 --> 01:11:06,053
[Mark] <i>Oh, it's, uh...
it's the future of delivery.</i>

1254
01:11:06,054 --> 01:11:07,888
<i>They've been training us
for months.</i>

1255
01:11:07,889 --> 01:11:09,556
<i>I need you to place
an official order on Amazon</i>

1256
01:11:09,557 --> 01:11:11,101
<i>- to activate the drone.</i>
- [sighs] This is nuts.

1257
01:11:17,899 --> 01:11:19,775
We only got one shot at this.

1258
01:11:19,776 --> 01:11:21,443
Are you sure
you can get it here?

1259
01:11:21,444 --> 01:11:23,028
<i>Don't worry. I fly like a bird.</i>

1260
01:11:23,029 --> 01:11:25,030
<i>I can soar like an eagle
with this thing.</i>

1261
01:11:25,031 --> 01:11:26,950
Okay, Mark. I believe in you.

1262
01:11:29,661 --> 01:11:30,996
<i>Will, are you seeing this?</i>

1263
01:11:32,497 --> 01:11:34,206
[William] Shit.

1264
01:11:34,207 --> 01:11:36,333
[reporter] <i>B-2 stealth bombers
are taking off</i>

1265
01:11:36,334 --> 01:11:38,502
<i>from Langley, Virginia
Air Force Base</i>

1266
01:11:38,503 --> 01:11:41,881
<i>and are estimated to strike
D.C. targets in ten minutes.</i>

1267
01:11:43,133 --> 01:11:45,009
[William] You got to move fast.

1268
01:11:45,010 --> 01:11:48,429
Now, Faith, I'm sending you
the blueprints to DHS.

1269
01:11:48,430 --> 01:11:50,848
You're gonna guide me
down to Goliath.

1270
01:11:50,849 --> 01:11:52,599
[sighs] <i>Okay, Dad.</i>

1271
01:11:52,600 --> 01:11:56,228
[William] I'm giving you all
full access to my system.

1272
01:11:56,229 --> 01:11:58,605
Sandra, I need you to be
my eyes and my ears.

1273
01:11:58,606 --> 01:12:02,318
- [Sandra] <i>Copy that.</i>
- [William] Let me know
what's going on at all times.

1274
01:12:04,946 --> 01:12:07,072
Okay. I'm out.

1275
01:12:07,073 --> 01:12:10,284
Hey, Mark.
Protect that sweet baby drone.

1276
01:12:10,285 --> 01:12:11,369
[Mark] <i>You got it, Pops.</i>

1277
01:12:17,667 --> 01:12:18,918
[ringtone playing]

1278
01:12:20,837 --> 01:12:21,838
<i>How we looking?</i>

1279
01:12:23,298 --> 01:12:24,799
<i>Oh, shit.</i>

1280
01:12:26,926 --> 01:12:29,094
[reporter] <i>Washington, D.C.
is being destroyed.</i>

1281
01:12:29,095 --> 01:12:32,222
<i>All machines seem to be headed
towards the DHS complex.</i>

1282
01:12:32,223 --> 01:12:34,683
[Sandra] <i>Will, they're headed
right your way.</i>

1283
01:12:34,684 --> 01:12:36,644
- [sirens blaring]
- [rumbling]

1284
01:12:39,230 --> 01:12:41,231
[William] <i>Sandra,
where are those bombers?</i>

1285
01:12:41,232 --> 01:12:42,317
[Sandra] <i>Hang on. Stand by.</i>

1286
01:12:46,988 --> 01:12:48,447
<i>About eight minutes out.</i>

1287
01:12:48,448 --> 01:12:50,115
[base commander]
<i>DHS is the last target.</i>

1288
01:12:50,116 --> 01:12:52,034
<i>-Hit it hard.</i>
- [pilot] <i>Roger that.</i>

1289
01:12:52,035 --> 01:12:55,371
<i>Initiating target lock on DHS
and surrounding threats.</i>

1290
01:12:56,372 --> 01:12:57,999
[Mark] <i>I'm heading out!</i>

1291
01:12:59,501 --> 01:13:00,960
<i>Incoming!</i>

1292
01:13:01,795 --> 01:13:05,839
- [loud electronic humming]
<i>- Guys, I need some cover here.</i>

1293
01:13:05,840 --> 01:13:08,801
[David] <i>Faith, get me
an access code
to a Reaper drone now.</i>

1294
01:13:08,802 --> 01:13:10,761
[Faith] <i>Dad, how do I get that?</i>

1295
01:13:10,762 --> 01:13:13,180
<i>Right click on the map.
Select "show active drones."</i>

1296
01:13:13,181 --> 01:13:15,891
- [Faith] <i>Roger that.</i>
- [Mark] <i>Guys,
I need some cover here!</i>

1297
01:13:15,892 --> 01:13:17,476
<i>- I got a bogey on my tail!</i>
- [Faith] <i>Okay, Dave.</i>

1298
01:13:17,477 --> 01:13:18,811
<i>I'm sending you
the closest one now.</i>

1299
01:13:18,812 --> 01:13:20,896
<i>Give me one second.</i>

1300
01:13:20,897 --> 01:13:22,856
<i>- Oh, shit. Shit.</i>
- [Faith] <i>You got to hurry, Dave.</i>

1301
01:13:22,857 --> 01:13:25,067
[David]
<i>Just a few more seconds.</i>

1302
01:13:25,068 --> 01:13:27,319
[Mark] <i>This thing's on my tail.
A little help here, please.</i>

1303
01:13:27,320 --> 01:13:28,738
<i>Don't worry, I got your back.</i>

1304
01:13:29,656 --> 01:13:32,199
<i>Dave, get this thing off me.
I can't shake him.</i>

1305
01:13:32,200 --> 01:13:33,826
<i>- Uh-huh. On your tail.</i>
- [Faith] <i>Come on, babe.</i>

1306
01:13:33,827 --> 01:13:35,285
- [David] <i>Go under.</i>
- [Faith] <i>You got it.</i>

1307
01:13:35,286 --> 01:13:37,246
[David]
<i>Okay, I got him. I got him.</i>

1308
01:13:37,247 --> 01:13:39,164
<i>Okay, you have another one
coming right up behind you.</i>

1309
01:13:39,165 --> 01:13:40,707
- [Mark] <i>Dave, do a barrel roll.</i>
- [Faith] <i>Oh, you got it, babe.</i>

1310
01:13:40,708 --> 01:13:42,000
- [Mark] <i>Barrel roll.</i>
- [Faith] <i>Come on.</i>

1311
01:13:42,001 --> 01:13:43,544
[Mark] <i>Lock on it, Dave.</i>

1312
01:13:43,545 --> 01:13:45,546
<i>- I'm gonna get him.</i>
- [Faith] <i>Come on.</i>

1313
01:13:45,547 --> 01:13:46,964
<i>Hurry, Mark.</i>

1314
01:13:46,965 --> 01:13:48,715
<i>- Yes! There it is.
- Okay, Mark.</i>

1315
01:13:48,716 --> 01:13:51,135
<i>- The coast is clear now. Hurry!
- Sure. Sure.</i>

1316
01:13:51,136 --> 01:13:53,262
<i>- Uh...
- Oh, shit.</i>

1317
01:13:53,263 --> 01:13:55,430
[Mark]
<i>Shit! No, no, no, no, no, no!</i>

1318
01:13:55,431 --> 01:13:57,182
<i>- Goddamn it.</i>
- [David] <i>Mark, Mark,
Mark, get it back up!</i>

1319
01:13:57,183 --> 01:13:58,725
<i>- Shit!</i>
- [Mark] <i>Uh...</i>

1320
01:13:58,726 --> 01:14:00,394
<i>- It-it's not working.
- Flip it over.</i>

1321
01:14:00,395 --> 01:14:02,354
<i>- Flip it over!
- It-it won't turn over.</i>

1322
01:14:02,355 --> 01:14:04,273
<i>Like a damn turtle
on its back here.</i>

1323
01:14:04,274 --> 01:14:05,858
<i>Okay, I got an idea.</i>

1324
01:14:05,859 --> 01:14:07,317
<i>Come on, guys.
I'm running out of time.</i>

1325
01:14:07,318 --> 01:14:08,986
[David] <i>Faith, get his number.</i>

1326
01:14:08,987 --> 01:14:10,696
[Faith] <i>I don't think
this guy has a phone.</i>

1327
01:14:10,697 --> 01:14:12,698
[David] <i>I mean, he must have
a phone. Everyone has a phone.</i>

1328
01:14:12,699 --> 01:14:14,491
[Mark] <i>Oh, my God. Come on.</i>

1329
01:14:14,492 --> 01:14:16,118
[David]
<i>Tell him to flip the drone.</i>

1330
01:14:16,119 --> 01:14:18,620
- [loud electronic humming]
- [siren whooping]

1331
01:14:18,621 --> 01:14:19,914
[Faith]
<i>Come on, come on, come on.</i>

1332
01:14:22,417 --> 01:14:23,668
[Mark]
<i>What's he doing? Come on.</i>

1333
01:14:25,795 --> 01:14:27,629
<i>You can do it. Come on,
come on, come on, come on.</i>

1334
01:14:27,630 --> 01:14:30,591
<i>Just... just flip it over.
Just...</i>

1335
01:14:30,592 --> 01:14:32,468
[Faith] <i>Wait, wait, wait.
Hold on.
I've got a better idea.</i>

1336
01:14:36,472 --> 01:14:37,890
[David] <i>Why is he waiting?</i>

1337
01:14:37,891 --> 01:14:40,017
<i>- What's going on?</i>
- [Faith] <i>Ugh!</i>

1338
01:14:40,018 --> 01:14:41,685
[Mark] <i>Wait.
Wait, wait, uh, g-give him, uh,</i>

1339
01:14:41,686 --> 01:14:44,229
<i>an Amazon gift card
for a thousand bucks.</i>

1340
01:14:44,230 --> 01:14:47,150
[panting] <i>Hurry! Come on.</i>

1341
01:14:49,277 --> 01:14:52,196
<i>- Yes! Oh, my God.</i>
- [electronic whirring]

1342
01:14:52,197 --> 01:14:53,822
<i>Come on, come on, come on.</i>

1343
01:14:53,823 --> 01:14:55,449
[Mark] <i>All right,
now, now, now, now, now!</i>

1344
01:14:55,450 --> 01:14:57,034
<i>Move, move, move, move!</i>

1345
01:14:57,035 --> 01:14:59,287
<i>Flip over for me, baby.
Come on. Come on, yes!</i>

1346
01:15:00,997 --> 01:15:02,957
[loud electronic humming]

1347
01:15:04,792 --> 01:15:06,668
[William] <i>Talk to me, Goose.
How we looking?</i>

1348
01:15:06,669 --> 01:15:08,755
<i>Under control, Pops.</i>

1349
01:15:09,464 --> 01:15:11,465
<i>Okay, which way?</i>

1350
01:15:11,466 --> 01:15:14,093
<i>Dad, I've never
used this before.
Give me a sec.</i>

1351
01:15:15,178 --> 01:15:18,723
<i>Gotcha.
Okay, the door is right
in front of you. Hurry!</i>

1352
01:15:21,100 --> 01:15:22,643
[base commander]
<i>Begin strike formation.</i>

1353
01:15:22,644 --> 01:15:24,603
<i>Five minutes to DHS target.</i>

1354
01:15:24,604 --> 01:15:26,605
[Sandra] <i>Guys, the bombers
are five minutes out.</i>

1355
01:15:26,606 --> 01:15:28,190
<i>You've got to hurry.</i>

1356
01:15:28,191 --> 01:15:29,983
- [William groans]
- [Mark] <i>Uh...</i>

1357
01:15:29,984 --> 01:15:31,944
<i>Dave, Dave, uh,
I need some help here.</i>

1358
01:15:31,945 --> 01:15:33,488
[David] <i>I got you, brother.
Don't worry, I got your back.</i>

1359
01:15:34,447 --> 01:15:36,740
<i>Okay. I got missile locked.</i>

1360
01:15:36,741 --> 01:15:38,659
<i>Firing.</i>

1361
01:15:38,660 --> 01:15:40,285
<i>- Damn! I'm out of missiles.</i>
- [Mark] <i>I need some help.</i>

1362
01:15:40,286 --> 01:15:41,870
<i>Someone think
of something fast.</i>

1363
01:15:41,871 --> 01:15:43,455
- [David] <i>You got it.
- Bait and switch.</i>

1364
01:15:43,456 --> 01:15:44,748
- [exhales heavily]
- [Mark] <i>I'll be the decoy.</i>

1365
01:15:44,749 --> 01:15:45,874
<i>- You got this.</i>
- [David] <i>Wait.</i>

1366
01:15:45,875 --> 01:15:47,376
<i>Wait, I-I got an idea.</i>

1367
01:15:47,377 --> 01:15:49,586
[whooshing]

1368
01:15:49,587 --> 01:15:50,588
<i>Boom!</i>

1369
01:15:51,881 --> 01:15:54,132
[Mark] <i>Holy crap! Badass.</i>

1370
01:15:54,133 --> 01:15:55,926
<i>Go off, Dave.</i>

1371
01:15:55,927 --> 01:15:57,427
[Faith] <i>There should be
a staircase on the left,</i>

1372
01:15:57,428 --> 01:15:58,887
